{"title_page": "Suicide of Amanda Todd", "text_new": "{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{short description|suicide of a Canadian student that took place on October 10, 2012}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox event\n| image                    = AmandaToddVideo.jpg\n| image_alt                = A girl in her mid-teens holding a cut-out piece of paper or card with the words \"I have nobody, I need someone\" and a sad emoticon written on it.\n| caption                  = A screenshot of Todd's YouTube video\n| date                     = {{start date|2012|10|10}}\n| location                 = [[Port Coquitlam]], British Columbia, Canada\n| cause                    = Hanging\n| inquest                  = British Columbia Coroners Service\n| coroner                  = Barb McLintock<ref name=\"Fox\">{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/|title=Canadian teen found dead weeks after posting wrenching YouTube video detailing bullying|date=October 12, 2012|accessdate=April 21, 2013|work=Fox News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607165008/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/|archivedate=June 7, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| suspects                 = Aydin Coban<ref name= \"CBC Coyban\"/>\n| charges                  = Indecent assault and child pornography (Netherlands)<ref name=\"Suspect\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140421074026/http://news.msn.com/crime-justice/dutch-mans-case-linked-to-amanda-todd Dutch man's case linked to Amanda Todd], ''MSN.com'', 18 April 2014, Hainsworth, J., Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref>\n}}\n'''Amanda Michelle Todd''' (November 27, 1996 \u2013 October 10, 2012)<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cahute|first1=Larissa|title=Amanda Todd: Hundreds hear tributes from family, friends, teachers|url=https://theprovince.com/news/Amanda+Todd+Hundreds+hear+tributes+from+family+friends+teachers/7568025/story.html|accessdate=November 13, 2016|work=[[The Province]]|date=November 19, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120112208/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Amanda+Todd+Hundreds+hear+tributes+from+family+friends+teachers/7568025/story.html|archivedate=November 20, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Martins|first1=Monisha|title=Amanda Todd celebrated in 'the birthday party she wanted'|url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/179887911.html|accessdate=November 13, 2016|work=[[Tri-City News]]|date=November 18, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121216054345/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/179887911.html|archivedate=December 16, 2012}}</ref> was a 15-year-old Canadian student and victim of [[cyberbullying]] who [[suicide by hanging|hanged herself]] at her home in [[Port Coquitlam]], a city in the province of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]]. Before her death, Todd posted a video on [[YouTube]] in which she used a series of flash cards to tell her experience of being blackmailed into exposing her breasts via webcam,<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> and of being bullied and physically assaulted. The video went [[Viral video|viral]] after her death,<ref name=\"cbccareport\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/story/2012/11/18/bc-amanda-todd-celebration-of-life.html |title=Amanda Todd tribute honours life of bullied teen |place=Calgary, CA |publisher=[[CBC.ca|CBC]] |work=News |date=November 18, 2012 |accessdate=November 24, 2012 |quote=After she died, the video gained worldwide recognition and registered more than six million hits, and copies of the video re-posted to YouTube have since gained at least 16 million additional hits. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121121030651/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/story/2012/11/18/bc-amanda-todd-celebration-of-life.html |archivedate=November 21, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> resulting in international media attention. The video has had more than 13 million views as of October 2019.<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> The [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] and British Columbia Coroners Service launched investigations into the suicide.\n\nIn response to her death, [[Christy Clark]], the [[Premier of British Columbia]], made an online statement of condolence and suggested a national discussion on criminalizing [[cyberbullying]].<ref>{{cite news|title=RCMP launch investigation into death of bullied BC teen|place=CA|url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/rcmp-launch-investigation-into-death-of-bullied-b-c-teen-1.993029|accessdate=October 13, 2012|newspaper=CTV News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013030309/http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/rcmp-launch-investigation-into-death-of-bullied-b-c-teen-1.993029|archivedate=October 13, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=After Amanda Todd's death, Christy Clark says new laws may be needed to combat bullying|url=https://vancouversun.com/life/After+Amanda+Todd+death+Christy+Clark+says+laws+needed+combat/7384108/story.html|publisher=Vancouver Sun|accessdate=October 13, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015002318/http://www.vancouversun.com/life/After+Amanda+Todd+death+Christy+Clark+says+laws+needed+combat/7384108/story.html|archivedate=October 15, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 24, 2001}}</ref> Also, a motion was introduced in the Canadian House of Commons to propose a study of the scope of bullying in Canada, and for more funding and support for anti-bullying organizations. Todd's mother Carol established the Amanda Todd Trust, receiving donations to support anti-bullying awareness education and programs for young people with mental health problems.\n\n==Background and suicide==\nOn September 7, 2012, Todd posted a 9-minute [[YouTube]] video titled ''My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm'', which showed her using a series of [[flashcards]] to tell of her experiences being bullied.<ref name=\"Video\">{{YouTube|vOHXGNx-E7E|My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm}}, 7 September 2012, Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref> The video went viral after her death on October 10, 2012, receiving over 1,600,000 views by October 13, 2012,<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tormenters-target-b-c-teen-amanda-todd-s-online-memorials-1.994594 |title=Online bullying of B.C. teen continues amid police probe &#124; CTV News |publisher=Ctvnews.ca |date=October 13, 2012 |accessdate=October 14, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713125954/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tormenters-target-amanda-todd-s-online-memorials-amid-police-probe-1.994594 |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> with news websites from around the world linking to it.\n[[File:Amanda Todd - 01.jpg|thumb|left|Facebook photo of Todd]]\n\nDuring the video, Todd writes that when she was in grade 7 (2009\u201310), around the same time she moved in with her father,<ref name=\"VancouverSun\" /> she used [[video chat]] to meet new people over the Internet and received compliments on her looks.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\">[http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU Amanda Todd - Transcript of video] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121210215745/http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU |date=December 10, 2012 }}, ''Pastebin.com'', 15 October 2012, Huntley, R., Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref> A stranger convinced Todd to bare her breasts on camera (an exploitative phenomenon known as \"capping\", short for [[screen shot|screen capturing]]),<ref name=\"Capping\">{{cite web | url=http://www.mapleridgenews.com/breaking_news/175880591.html | title=Predators lurk behind computer screens | publisher=Maple Ridge News | author=Martins, Monisha | accessdate=2016-09-13 | date=2016-10-26 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926201721/http://www.mapleridgenews.com/breaking_news/175880591.html | archivedate=September 26, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> after attempting to do so for a year.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> He later blackmailed her by threatening to give the topless photo to her friends unless she gave him a \"show\";<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\">{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/10/12/world/americas/canada-teen-bullying/index.html?iref=allsearch |title=Bullied Canadian teen leaves behind chilling YouTube video \u2013 CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date=October 13, 2012 |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026003136/http://edition.cnn.com/2012/10/12/world/americas/canada-teen-bullying/index.html?iref=allsearch |archivedate=October 26, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> she also featured briefly on the faux animated news show ''Daily Capper'' on BlogTV  in an incident that attracted the vigilante attentions of the group [[Anonymous (group)|Anonymous]] after her suicide.<ref name=\"Daily Capper\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/society/sick-pedophile-ring-blackmail-amanda-todd/|title=Inside the sick pedophile ring that blackmailed girls like Amanda Todd|last=Morris|first=Kevin|date=2012-10-19|website=The Daily Dot|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817110141/http://www.dailydot.com/society/sick-pedophile-ring-blackmail-amanda-todd/|archivedate=August 17, 2016|url-status=live|accessdate=2016-09-15|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Anonymous, Daily Capper, and Kody1206\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/in-the-darkest-corners-of-the-internet-bullies-and-predators-hide-in-plain-sight/article4650771/ | title=In the darkest corners of the Internet, bullies and predators hide in plain sight | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2012-10-25 | accessdate=2016-09-15 | author=Woo, Andrea | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010084738/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/in-the-darkest-corners-of-the-internet-bullies-and-predators-hide-in-plain-sight/article4650771/ | archivedate=October 10, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> An episode of ''Daily Capper'' that attempted to take the moral high ground, very different in tone from their usual material, was released a month after her death.<ref name=\"The Suspicious Return of the Daily Capper\">{{cite web | url=https://www.vice.com/en_ca/read/the-suspicious-return-of-the-daily-capper | title=The Suspicious Return of the Daily Capper | publisher=Vice | date=2012-11-12 | accessdate=2016-09-15 | author=McGuire, Patrick | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505095940/http://www.vice.com/en_ca/read/the-suspicious-return-of-the-daily-capper | archivedate=May 5, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nTodd wrote that during the Christmas 2010 break, police informed her at 4:00&nbsp;a.m. that the photo was circulating on the Internet.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> She wrote that she experienced [[anxiety]], [[depression (mood)|depression]], and [[panic disorder]] due to having been sexually exploited online and cyberbullied.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Her family moved to a new home, where Todd later said she began using alcohol and other drugs.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\" />\n\nA year later, Todd's blackmailer reappeared, creating a [[Facebook]] profile that used the topless photo as its profile image and contacting classmates at her new school.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Again, Todd was teased, eventually changing schools for a second time.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> She wrote that she began chatting to \"an old guy friend\" who contacted her.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> The friend invited Todd to his house, where they had sex while his girlfriend was on holiday.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Villalva|first=Brittney R.|title=Amanda Todd: 15-Year-Old Tells Story of Bullying and Suicide Before Death|url=http://global.christianpost.com/news/amanda-todd-15-year-old-tells-story-of-bullying-and-suicide-before-death-video-83253/|work=The Christian Post|accessdate=October 16, 2012|date=October 14, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102192909/http://global.christianpost.com/news/amanda-todd-15-year-old-tells-story-of-bullying-and-suicide-before-death-video-83253/|archivedate=January 2, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The following week, the boy's girlfriend and a group of about 15 others confronted Todd at school, shouting insults, with the boy's girlfriend punching her;<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Todd fell to the ground, then lay in a ditch, where her father found her.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> After the attack, Todd attempted suicide by drinking bleach, but survived after being rushed to hospital to have her stomach pumped.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\" /> \"It killed me inside and I thought I was gonna actully{{sic}} die\", Todd commented in her video.<ref name=\"Fox\" /><ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" />\n\nAfter returning home, Todd discovered abusive messages about her suicide attempt posted to Facebook.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> In March, 2012, her family moved to another city to start afresh, but Todd was unable to escape the past.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> According to her mother, \"Every time she moved schools he would go undercover and become a Facebook friend. What the guy did was he went online to the kids who went to [the new school] and said that he was going to be a new student \u2014 that he was starting school the following week and that he wanted some friends and could they friend him on Facebook. He eventually gathered people's names and sent Todd's video to her new school\", including students, teachers and parents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vancouversun.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7384521/story.html|title=Amanda Todd's mother speaks out about her daughter, bullying (with video)|author=Gillian Shaw|date=October 14, 2012|work=Vancouver Sun|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031121155/http://www.vancouversun.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7384521/story.html|archivedate=October 31, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Six months later, further messages and abuse were still being posted to social networking sites. With Todd's mental state worsening, she began to engage in [[Self-harm|self-mutilation]] and cutting.<ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Despite taking her prescribed antidepressants and receiving counseling, she overdosed and was hospitalized for two days.<ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Keneally|first=Meghan|title=Tragedy as girl, 15, kills herself just one month after posting desperate YouTube plea begging bullies to stop tormenting her|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2216543/Amanda-Todd-Canadian-teen-kills-desperate-video-plea-begging-bullies-stop.html|publisher=Daily Mail|accessdate=October 13, 2012|location=London|date=October 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20121013084629/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2216543/Amanda-Todd-Canadian-teen-kills-desperate-video-plea-begging-bullies-stop.html|archivedate=October 13, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTodd was taunted by other students at her school for her low grades, a consequence of a [[language-based learning disability]], and for the time she spent in hospital to treat her severe depression.<ref name=\"VancouverSun\">{{cite news|last=Shaw|first=Gillian|title='She shared everything with me': Amanda Todd's mother talks about her life with her daughter|url=https://vancouversun.com/health/shared+everything+with+Amanda+Todd+mother+talks+about+life/7419475/story.html|accessdate=October 21, 2012|newspaper=vancouversun.com|date=October 20, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022210457/http://www.vancouversun.com/health/shared+everything+with+Amanda+Todd+mother+talks+about+life/7419475/story.html|archivedate=October 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \"It didn't really help that after she got out of the hospital recently some kids started calling her 'psycho' and saying she had been in the crazy hospital,\" her mother said. \"She went to the hospital, she had therapy, she had counseling, she was on a good track. On the day she gets out, that happens. I shake my head and I think, 'Are kids really that nasty, do they really not think, what if it was them?'\"<ref name=\"VancouverSun\" />\n\nOn October 10, 2012, at about 6:00&nbsp;PM ([[Pacific Daylight Time|PDT]]), Todd was found hanging at her home.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/amanda-todd-suicide-girls-mum-1379909|title=Amanda Todd: Suicide girl's mum reveals more harrowing details of cyber bullying campaign that drove her daughter to her death|last=Bleaney|first=Rob|date=2012-10-15|work=mirror|access-date=2018-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623034852/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/amanda-todd-suicide-girls-mum-1379909|archive-date=June 23, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Port Coquitlam teen driven to death by cyberbullying (with video)|url=https://montrealgazette.com/technology/Port+Coquitlam+teen+driven+death+cyberbullying+with+video/7375941/story.html|accessdate=October 15, 2012|newspaper=Vancouver Sun|date=October 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015020557/http://www.montrealgazette.com/technology/Port+Coquitlam+teen+driven+death+cyberbullying+with+video/7375941/story.html|archivedate=October 15, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At the time of her death, Todd was a [[Tenth grade|grade 10]] student<ref name=\"washingtonpost1\">{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/ |title=Canadian teen found dead weeks after posting wrenching YouTube video detailing bullying |publisher=Fox News |date=2012-10-12 |accessdate=October 31, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031180509/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/ |archivedate=October 31, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> at CABE Secondary in Coquitlam,<ref>{{cite web |last=Luymes |first=Glenda |url=https://theprovince.com/news/Cyberbullying+Amanda+Todd+suicide+prompts+grief/7376942/story.html |title=Cyberbullying: Outpouring of grief over teen's suicide (with video) |publisher=The province |date=March 25, 2002 |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014091826/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Cyberbullying+Amanda+Todd+suicide+prompts+grief/7376942/story.html |archivedate=October 14, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> a school that caters to students who have experienced social and behaviour issues in previous educational settings.<ref>{{cite web | title = About CABE | url = http://www.sd43.bc.ca/secondary/CABE/About/Pages/ | publisher = sd43 | accessdate = November 5, 2012 | location = BC, CA }}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== Investigation, arrest and conviction ==\n\nA preliminary investigation by British Columbia Coroners Service showed that Todd's death was a suicide. The cause of death was reported in some media as hanging,<ref name=\"Penny\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/its-too-late-for-amanda-todd-but-we-must-out-the-cyberbullies-8217004.html|title=It's too late for Amanda Todd, but we must out the cyber-bullies \u2013 Comment \u2013 Voices \u2013 The Independent|last=Penny|first=Laurie|date=October 18, 2012|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, a 15-year-old Canadian schoolgirl hanged herself, last week, after years of unrelenting abuse by peers and online predators, one of whom persuaded her to flash her breasts and then shared the picture around the world.|location=London|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122145733/http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/its-too-late-for-amanda-todd-but-we-must-out-the-cyberbullies-8217004.html|archivedate=November 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Agomuoh\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/amanda-todd-suicide-doesnt-end-cyber-torment-ridiculed-teen-846827|title=Amanda Todd Suicide Doesn't End Cyber Torment For Ridiculed Teen|last=Agomuoh|first=Fionna|date=October 15, 2012|work=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd of British Columbia apparently hanged herself on Oct. 10 after a grave mistake followed her for the rest of her brief life.|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130316173856/http://www.ibtimes.com/amanda-todd-suicide-doesnt-end-cyber-torment-ridiculed-teen-846827|archivedate=March 16, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Ryall\">{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/world/online-bully-victim-amanda-todd-still-tormented-in-death/story-fndir2ev-1226497411838|title=Anonymous outs bully they claim drove Amanda Todd to suicide, mum says leave her family alone &#124;News.com.au|last=Ryall|first=Jenni|date=October 17, 2012|work=[[News Limited]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, from Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, was found hanged in her home on October 10, weeks after she uploaded a video to YouTube that describes \u2013 via a series of note cards \u2013 her treatment at the hands of a cyber bully.|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114052415/http://www.news.com.au/world/online-bully-victim-amanda-todd-still-tormented-in-death/story-fndir2ev-1226497411838|archivedate=November 14, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Dufour\">{{cite news|last=Dufour|first=Katinka|title=Amanda Todd case highlights issue of online bullying|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9612030/Amanda-Todd-case-highlights-issue-of-online-bullying.html|accessdate=November 11, 2012|newspaper=telegraph.co.uk|date=October 16, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, was found hanged in her home in Port Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada, last Wednesday, one month before her 16th birthday.|location=London|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121018195156/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9612030/Amanda-Todd-case-highlights-issue-of-online-bullying.html|archivedate=October 18, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> but the exact cause of death had not been released.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd was not internet obsessed, mother says|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/amanda-todd-was-not-internet-obsessed-mother-says-1.1190867|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=May 25, 2014|date=October 23, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525202706/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/amanda-todd-was-not-internet-obsessed-mother-says-1.1190867|archivedate=May 25, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) and British Columbia Coroners Service put 20 full-time investigators on the case.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> The Coquitlam and Ridge Meadows serious crime teams cooperated in a full investigation, conducting interviews and examining factors that may have contributed to Todd's death.<ref name=\"globaltvbc.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltvbc.com/rcmp+launch+full+investigation+into+amanda+todds+death/6442732749/story.html |title=Global BC &#124; RCMP launch full investigation into Amanda Todd's death |publisher=Globaltvbc.com |date= |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015023057/http://www.globaltvbc.com/rcmp+launch+full+investigation+into+amanda+todds+death/6442732749/story.html |archivedate=October 15, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Investigators are reviewing content at social media sites and actively monitoring pages.<ref name=\"globaltvbc.com\" />\n\nThe Canadian national organization [[Cybertip.ca]] reported having received a tip about Todd nearly a year before her suicide. The anti-child-exploitation group stated that, in November 2011, a concerned citizen reported that images of Todd were in circulation on the Internet. That information was provided to law enforcement as well as child welfare agencies.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/15/bc-amanda-todd-tormentor-anonymous.html Amanda Todd's alleged tormentor named by hacker group - British Columbia - CBC News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016104520/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/15/bc-amanda-todd-tormentor-anonymous.html |date=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> According to the CBC news program ''[[The Fifth Estate (TV)|The Fifth Estate]]'', the RCMP were repeatedly informed that the juvenile was being sexually extorted by an adult male, and in response the RCMP told the family there was \"nothing that could be done\" about it.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suicide-rcmp-repeatedly-told-of-blackmailer-s-attempts-1.2427097|title=Amanda Todd suicide: RCMP repeatedly told of blackmailer's attempts|date=15 November 2013|accessdate=19 April 2014|work=CBC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217180217/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suicide-rcmp-repeatedly-told-of-blackmailer-s-attempts-1.2427097|archivedate=February 17, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> According to the Ontario Provincial Police (OPP), however, the crime of \"sextortion\" can be investigated quite successfully.{{Citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n\nFollowing an investigation by [[Facebook]]'s security unit, whose report was forwarded by U.S. authorities to the [[Child Exploitation and Online Protection Centre]] attached to the British [[National Crime Agency]],<ref name=\"Facebook security unit.\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/on-the-trail-of-amanda-todds-alleged-tormentor/article18935075/?page=all | title=On the trail of Amanda Todd's alleged tormentor | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2014-05-31 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=White, Patrick | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129024135/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/on-the-trail-of-amanda-todds-alleged-tormentor/article18935075/?page=all | archivedate=January 29, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and then to Dutch authorities, in January 2014 Dutch police arrested a man in a case involving multiple victims in the Netherlands, U.K., and Canada, having installed [[spyware]] on his computers; \"chilling\" chat logs of extortion, numerous images of child pornography, and 5,800 bookmarked names that served as a database of potential victims and their social networks were found.<ref name=\"De Visser\">{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/16/15-year-old-amanda-todd-s-alleged-sextortionist-on-trial-at-last.html |title=Sextortion 15-Year-Old Amanda Todd's Alleged Sextortionist on Trial at Last |last=De Visser |first=Nadette |date=February 16, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Daily Beast]] |access-date=March 10, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312072158/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/16/15-year-old-amanda-todd-s-alleged-sextortionist-on-trial-at-last.html |archivedate=March 12, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In April 2014, it was reported that Dutch authorities charged a 35-year-old man of dual Dutch and Turkish citizenship (identified only as \"Aydin C.\" within the Netherlands<ref name=\"Suspect\" /><ref>[http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/who-is-the-dutch-man-arrested-in-connection-with-the-death-of-amanda-todd-1.1781755 Who is the Dutch man arrested in connection with the death of Amanda Todd?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901183951/http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/who-is-the-dutch-man-arrested-in-connection-with-the-death-of-amanda-todd-1.1781755 |date=September 1, 2014 }}, [[CTV News]], April 18, 2014</ref> in accordance with Dutch privacy laws) with indecent assault and child pornography.<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> That same month, the RCMP announced that the man had been charged with extortion, internet luring, criminal harassment and possession and distribution of child pornography for his alleged offenses against Todd and other child victims, both male and female.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/news/story/1.2614034 | work=CBC News | title=Amanda Todd case: RCMP detail 5 charges against Dutch citizen | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419101916/http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/news/story/1.2614034 | archivedate=April 19, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Todd's mother thanked police, but also said that she believed more than one person was involved.<ref>{{cite news|website=BBC|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27076991|title=Man charged in Netherlands in Amanda Todd suicide case|date=18 April 2014|accessdate=18 April 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419022314/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27076991|archivedate=April 19, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On January 28, 2015, [[CBC News]] said that Aydin Coban had written an open letter proclaiming his innocence.<ref name=\"CBC Coyban\">{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd suspect Aydin Coban writes open letter proclaiming innocence|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suspect-aydin-coban-writes-open-letter-proclaiming-innocence-1.2935055|website=cbc.ca|publisher=[[CBC News]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709235902/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suspect-aydin-coban-writes-open-letter-proclaiming-innocence-1.2935055|archivedate=July 9, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nDutch authorities dropped some child pornography charges in October 2015;<ref name=\"Netherlands drops child porn charges against man also accused in Amanda Todd case\">{{cite web | url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2015/10/27/netherlands-drops-child-porn-charges-in-amanda-todd-case.html | title=Netherlands drops child porn charges against man also accused in Amanda Todd case Dutch prosecutor has dropped child pornography charges that relate to accused's alleged non-Dutch victims, suspect's lawyer says. | publisher=thestar.com | date=2015-10-27 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Kestler-D\u2019Amours, Jillian | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320091549/https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2015/10/27/netherlands-drops-child-porn-charges-in-amanda-todd-case.html | archivedate=March 20, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Extradition to proceed in Amanda Todd case\">{{cite web | url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/extradition-to-proceed-in-amanda-todd-case-1.2096989 | title=Extradition to proceed in Amanda Todd case: Decision by Dutch authorities to leave the Todd case out of legal proceedings not expected to affect court case here regarding Port Coquitlam teen. | publisher=Tri-City News | date=2015-10-27 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Strandberg, Diane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919074553/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/extradition-to-proceed-in-amanda-todd-case-1.2096989 | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Coban's case went to trial in February 2017, and concluded on March 16, 2017. He faced 72 charges of sexual assault and extortion in the Netherlands involving 39 alleged victims (34 young women and five men in countries as various as Britain, Canada, Norway and the United States, some of whom had been harassed for years); eventually convicted and sentenced on the Dutch charges of internet fraud and blackmail, he faces five separate Canadian charges related to Todd (herself not one of the 39), and it was anticipated that he would be [[extradition|extradited]] to Canada no sooner than the middle of 2018 whilst serving his Dutch sentence of 10 years and 8 months. Carol Todd expressed relief at the sentence.<ref name=\"De Visser\"/><ref name=\"Dutch Coban Trial\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39295474 |title=Amanda Todd case: Accused Dutch man jailed for cyberbullying |date=2017-03-16 |website=BBC |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317084824/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39295474 |archivedate=March 17, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In December 2019, it was reported that Canadian authorities were preparing for the extradition.<ref>https://globalnews.ca/news/6323357/potential-extradition-amanda-todd-accused-tormentor/</ref>\n\n==Reaction==\nTodd's suicide received widespread international media coverage, much of which included a link to her YouTube video and an email address provided by the RCMP appealing for information from the public. Within 24 hours of the appeal, over 400 tips were received.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> The RCMP has stated that its investigation was hindered by the amount of false information in online postings after Todd's death, and by scams claiming to raise money for her family.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/16/bc-amanda-todd-scam-websites.html|title=Amanda Todd probe delayed by online rumours, scams|publisher=CBC.ca|author=Alan Waterman, Canadian Press|date=October 17, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019000816/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/16/bc-amanda-todd-scam-websites.html|archivedate=October 19, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 19, 2012, a series of vigils was held across Canada and internationally to remember Todd and other victims of bullying.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/10/18/toronto-bullying-silence.html|title=Bullying victims remembered in vigils worldwide:Vigils, memorials follow suicide of B.C. teen Amanda Todd last week|publisher=CBC.ca|date=October 19, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020004820/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/10/18/toronto-bullying-silence.html|archivedate=October 20, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> A [[minute of silence]] was observed by a quarter of a million students in the [[Toronto District School Board]] district.<ref>{{cite news|last=Brown|first=Louise|title=Amanda Todd: Toronto students to remember bullied teen who committed suicide|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1273960--amanda-todd-toronto-students-to-remember-bullied-teen-who-committed-suicide|accessdate=October 20, 2012|newspaper=Toronto Star|date=October 18, 2012|location=Toronto ON|page=2|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021011923/http://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1273960--amanda-todd-toronto-students-to-remember-bullied-teen-who-committed-suicide|archivedate=October 21, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The same day, Todd's mother was a guest of the 2012 [[We Day]] event in Vancouver, a week after Todd's death. Bullying had been scheduled as a topic before Todd's death and was addressed by speakers [[Magic Johnson]], musician and anti-bullying advocate [[Demi Lovato]] and British Columbia Premier [[Christy Clark]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/news/Premier+tells+kids+stand+change+against+bullying/7410549/story.html |title=Amanda Todd's death felt at We Day event in Vancouver |publisher=The Province |date=October 19, 2012 |author=James Keller, Canadian Press |accessdate=October 19, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019141549/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Premier+tells+kids+stand+change+against+bullying/7410549/story.html |archivedate=October 19, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nInitially, Todd's mother was denied entry to an anti-bullying conference for fear that her presence would upset other attendees.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ferreras|first=Jesse|title=Amanda Todd's Mother, Carol Todd, Excluded From Anti-Bullying Conference|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/14/carol-todd-amanda-todd-mother-anti-bullying-conference_n_2130424.html|work=Huffpost British Columbia|publisher=HPMG News|accessdate=November 18, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118040209/http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/14/carol-todd-amanda-todd-mother-anti-bullying-conference_n_2130424.html|archivedate=November 18, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 14, 2012}}</ref> The family was invited to attend later events.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd Memorial Set For Sunday|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/17/amanda-todd-memorial_n_2151479.html|work=Huffpost British Columbia|publisher=HPMG News|accessdate=November 18, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119010742/http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/17/amanda-todd-memorial_n_2151479.html|archivedate=November 19, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn November 18, 2012, 600 people gathered at a final farewell ceremony for Todd at [[Red Robinson Show Theatre]] in Coquitlam, near her home. Carol Todd told the gathering that her daughter had left behind \"a larger-than-life message that has sparked the world and has made it open its eyes, its ears and its hearts\".<ref>[https://vancouversun.com/life/Amanda+Todd+honoured+hundreds+Coquitlam+memorial+service/7567970/story.html Amanda Todd honoured by hundreds at Coquitlam memorial service] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122000957/http://www.vancouversun.com/life/Amanda+Todd+honoured+hundreds+Coquitlam+memorial+service/7567970/story.html |date=November 22, 2012 }} Retrieved Nov 19, 2012</ref>\n\nInternet hacking and activist group [[Anonymous (group)|Anonymous]] alleged that a 32-year-old man was Todd's blackmailer and main tormentor. The group published the [[Vancouver]]-area man's name and address on the Internet, resulting in the man's receipt of online threats of vigilante justice.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" /> After investigating the tip, police determined that the allegations were unfounded, and said that \"false information that is being spread by people who appear to be trying to use Amanda's story to do harm or make a profit\" was one of the challenges they faced.<ref name=\"ottawacitizen\">{{Cite journal|last1=Shaw|last2=Sinoski|first1=Gillian|first2=Kelly|title=B.C. man denies harassing Amanda Todd; RCMP say allegations are 'unfounded'|journal=[[Ottawa Citizen]]|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/denies+harassing+Amanda+Todd+RCMP+allegations+unfounded/7400309/story.html|publisher=Postmedia Network Inc.|date=October 17, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021230743/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/denies+harassing+Amanda+Todd+RCMP+allegations+unfounded/7400309/story.html|archivedate=October 21, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAccording to an interview with the ''[[The Vancouver Sun|Vancouver Sun]]'', the publication of his identity on social media sites resulted in over 50 emails and thousands of Facebook death threats.<ref name=\"ottawacitizen\" /> A member of Anonymous had attempted to dissuade the group from publishing the information, saying that they had the right person but that the address belonged to someone else, not the target. ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]'' reported that the person who was responsible turned out to be 19, not 32.<ref name=\"inqtodd\">{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd Investigation: Police Say Anonymous Outed the Wrong Man|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/367540/amanda-todd-investigation-police-say-anonymous-outed-the-wrong-man/|publisher=inquisitr.com|accessdate=December 23, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225005441/http://www.inquisitr.com/367540/amanda-todd-investigation-police-say-anonymous-outed-the-wrong-man/|archivedate=December 25, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"globewoo\">{{cite news|last=Woo|first=Andrea|title='Hacktivist' group names second person in Amanda Todd case|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/hacktivist-group-names-second-person-in-amanda-todd-case/article4619867/|accessdate=December 23, 2012|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|date=October 17, 2012|location=Toronto|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222190944/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/hacktivist-group-names-second-person-in-amanda-todd-case/article4619867/|archivedate=December 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Mainstream media ===\nMichelle Dean of ''[[The New Yorker]]'' compared Todd's death to the [[suicide of Tyler Clementi]], an [[LGBT]] student at [[Rutgers University]] who jumped to his death from the [[George Washington Bridge]] after his roommate encouraged friends to watch a live stream of Clementi kissing another man. In an early piece questioning the assumptions of perpetrators of [[nonconsensual pornography]], she quotes [[Mary Anne Franks]]:{{quote|Women have become, as Franks put it, \"unwilling avatars\", unable to control their own images online, and then told to put up with it for the sake of \"freedom\", for the good of the community. And then they are incorrectly told, even if the public is behind them, that they have no remedies in the law. They are shouted down by people with a view of freedom of speech more literal than that held by any judge.}}\nand concludes:<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dean|first1=Michelle|title=The Story of Amanda Todd|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/the-story-of-amanda-todd|website=newyorker.com|publisher=[[The New Yorker]]|year=2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713103045/http://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/the-story-of-amanda-todd|archivedate=July 13, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>{{quote|...[But] whatever Amanda Todd might have been thinking, whatever else might be true, she did get one thing out of this: Amanda Todd did manage to, just once, tell her own story. She got to drown out the version of her that strangers had put out on the Web. It's a small comfort. But it was perhaps the only one she had left.}}\n\n''[[Vancouver Magazine]]'' titled a piece on Todd \"The Girl Who Woke Up the World\"; in 2012 she was the third-most [[Google]]d person, and by 2013 vigils had been held in 38 countries. Her mother continues to be the subject of cyber-stalking.<ref name=\"The Girl Who Woke Up The World\">{{cite web | url=http://vanmag.com/uncategorized/the-girl-who-woke-up-the-world-amanda-todd/ | title=The Girl Who Woke Up The World: Amanda Todd | publisher=Vancouver Magazine | date=2016-10-01 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170503011657/http://vanmag.com/uncategorized/the-girl-who-woke-up-the-world-amanda-todd/ | archivedate=May 3, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Social media===\nAfter Todd's suicide, more than one million Facebook users \"liked\" her Facebook memorial page.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Hewlett|first=Jason|title=Amanda Todd video put spotlight on bullying|url=http://www.kamloopsnews.ca/article/20130103/KAMLOOPS0101/121239984/-1/kamloops/story-of-the-year-amanda-todd-video-put-spotlight-on-bullying|work=kamloopsnews.ca|accessdate=April 12, 2013|date=January 3, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517033216/http://www.kamloopsnews.ca/article/20130103/KAMLOOPS0101/121239984/-1/kamloops/story-of-the-year-amanda-todd-video-put-spotlight-on-bullying|archivedate=May 17, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Mingled among the positive support and comments are attacks and images from strangers and people claiming to be her former classmates.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> After one man's derogatory Facebook comments about Todd's death were reported to his employer, the [[Grafton-Fraser]] Mr. Big & Tall clothing chain, it confirmed that he was no longer an employee.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ontario man loses job after writing cruel Facebook comment about Amanda Todd|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/2012/10/17/cruel-facebook-comment-about-amanda-todds-suicide-costs-man-his-job/|accessdate=November 4, 2012|newspaper=National Post Wire Services|date=Oct 17, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20121018183355/http://news.nationalpost.com/2012/10/17/cruel-facebook-comment-about-amanda-todds-suicide-costs-man-his-job/|archivedate=October 18, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Toronto man fired after 'trolling' Amanda Todd Facebook page|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/Toronto+fired+after+trolling+Amanda+Todd+Facebook+page/7397857/story.html|accessdate=November 4, 2012|newspaper=Ottawa Citizen|date=October 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106075103/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/Toronto+fired+after+trolling+Amanda+Todd+Facebook+page/7397857/story.html|archivedate=November 6, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 19, 2012, police in New Zealand said they were questioning a 17-year-old boy from [[Raglan, New Zealand|Raglan]] who allegedly posted \"inappropriate and disturbing images\" on a memorial page for Todd. Police removed the images and shut down the boy's Facebook page.<ref name=\"BNONews2012\">{{cite web |title=Police question New Zealand teen over Amanda Todd images |publisher=[[BNO News]] |date=October 19, 2012 |url=http://www.bnowire.com/?p=835 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130118074406/http://www.bnowire.com/?p=835 |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 18, 2013 |accessdate=October 20, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nTodd's suicide engendered the ''Drink Bleach'' [[Internet meme]] almost immediately,<ref name=\"Drink Bleach Meme\">{{cite web | url=http://www.vancouverobserver.com/life/technology/planet-trolls | title=Time to rip the mask of anonymity off online trolls | publisher=Vancouver Observer | date=2013-08-08 | accessdate=2016-09-16 | author=Garossino, Sandy | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913195250/http://www.vancouverobserver.com/life/technology/planet-trolls | archivedate=September 13, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and four years after her death she was associated with the 2016 movie ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'' (along with [[Adolf Hitler]], [[Robin Williams]] and [[Kurt Cobain]] in one depiction), a meme her mother regarded as unhelpful to those at risk.<ref name=\"Suicide Squad meme\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/suicide-squad-amanda-todd-1.3712615 | title=Internet meme for Suicide Squad film ridicules Amanda Todd's death, mom says: Carol Todd says she has shared the images to build awareness and discussion | publisher=The Canadian Press | date=2016-08-08 | accessdate=2016-09-16 | author=Burgmann, Tamsyn | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912052130/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/suicide-squad-amanda-todd-1.3712615 | archivedate=September 12, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Amanda Todd Legacy Society===\nCarol Todd established the Amanda Todd Trust at the [[Royal Bank of Canada]], receiving donations to support anti-bullying awareness education and programs for young people with mental health problems.<ref>{{cite web |last=Shaw |first=Gillian |url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7386696/story.html |title=Mother wants Amanda Todd's video to help others |publisher=Calgaryherald.com |date= |accessdate=October 14, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016070855/http://www.calgaryherald.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7386696/story.html |archivedate=October 16, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> (A week after Todd's death, [[ABC News]] reported that fraudulent websites had been set up claiming to solicit donations, quoting a statement by RCMP Sergeant Peter Thiessen: \"Taking advantage of a family's grief is despicable...We want to get the word out that there is one real account and anyone who is interested can make a donation at any RBC branch to the Amanda Todd Trust Account.\")<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/bullied-teen-amanda-todds-death-spurs-fake-fundraising/story?id=17507029|title=Bullied Teen's Death Spurs Fake Sites|date=October 18, 2012|publisher=ABC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130205192127/http://abcnews.go.com/US/bullied-teen-amanda-todds-death-spurs-fake-fundraising/story?id=17507029|archivedate=February 5, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It has since been incorporated as a nonprofit colloquially known as Amanda Todd Legacy, with a particular outreach on the mental health issues of adolescents on occasions such as [[World Mental Health Day]] on October 10.<ref name=\"World Mental Health Day\">{{cite web | url=http://org.kidshelpphone.ca/carol-todd-wants-you-to-lightuppurple-for-world-mental-health-day/ | title=Carol Todd wants you to #LightUpPurple for World Mental Health Day | publisher=Kids Help Phone | accessdate=2016-09-13 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919132912/http://org.kidshelpphone.ca/carol-todd-wants-you-to-lightuppurple-for-world-mental-health-day/ | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The Amanda Todd Legacy Award was established in conjunction with the [[Douglas College]] Foundation in 2016; three students are awarded $1,000 annually toward their studies.<ref name=\"Amanda Todd Legacy Award\">{{cite web | url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/new-amanda-todd-award-for-dc-students-1.2078111 | title=New Amanda Todd award for DC students: $1,000 award will be given to students enrolled in child and youth care program in recognition of Port Coquitlam teen and mental health issues | publisher=Tri-City News | date=2016-10-26 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Strandberg, Diane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919082350/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/new-amanda-todd-award-for-dc-students-1.2078111 | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Amanda Todd Legacy and Carol Todd have also participated in [[LGBT]] advocacy under the aegis of [[Kids Help Phone]], Canada's 24-hour [[hotline]] for youth in crisis.<ref name=\"Kids Help Phone Walk\">{{cite web | url=http://www.niagarafallsreview.ca/2015/07/17/everyone-can-make-a-difference | title=Everyone Can Made A Difference | publisher=Niagara Falls Review | date=2015-07-17 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Langley, Alison | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923132513/http://www.niagarafallsreview.ca/2015/07/17/everyone-can-make-a-difference | archive-date=September 23, 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nCarol Todd is close friends with Leah Parsons, the mother of [[Rehtaeh Parsons]], and they frequently network on cyberbullying issues. The two women often have speaking engagements about their respective daughters with an emphasis on respect, acceptance, forgiveness and dignity.<ref name=\"Friendship with Leah Parsons\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/forged-in-sadness-grieving-mothers-find-friendship/article17948255/ | title=Forged in sadness, grieving mothers find friendship | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2014-04-12 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Taber, Jane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920061807/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/forged-in-sadness-grieving-mothers-find-friendship/article17948255/ | archivedate=September 20, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, 2018, composer [[Jocelyn Morlock]] won the [[Juno Award]] for Classical Composition of the Year for a piece inspired by Amanda Todd; she was joined onstage by Carol Todd.<ref name=\"Juno Award for Classical Composition of the Year\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.cbc.ca/player/play/1194428995571 |title= Jocelyn Morlock wins Classical Composition of the Year |id= Juno Gala Dinner & Awards |date= 2018-03-24 |website= CBC Player |access-date= 2018-03-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180330060836/http://www.cbc.ca/player/play/1194428995571 |archive-date= March 30, 2018 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n\n===Legislative impact===\nIn 2012 parliamentarian [[Dany Morin]] of the [[New Democratic Party of Canada|New Democratic Party]] introduced a motion in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] in response to Todd's death. The motion proposed a study of the scope of bullying in Canada, and more funding and support for anti-bullying organizations. It was also intended to lay the groundwork for a national strategy to prevent bullying. Morin himself had experienced bullying in school.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/in-wake-of-amanda-todd-suicide-mps-to-debate-anti-bullying-motion-1.995254 |title= In wake of Amanda Todd suicide, MPs to debate anti-bullying motion |publisher=CTV News |date= October 14, 2012 |author=CTVNews.ca Staff |accessdate= October 17, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6MMlIcGEg?url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/in-wake-of-amanda-todd-suicide-mps-to-debate-anti-bullying-motion-1.995254 |archivedate= January 4, 2014 |df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013 Justice Minister [[Peter MacKay]] of the [[Conservative Party (Canada)|Conservative Party]] introduced Bill C-13, anti-cyberbullying and [[revenge porn]] legislation. Carol Todd criticized its warrantless access provisions, saying, \"I don't want to see our children victimized again by losing privacy rights\".<ref name=\"2013 Bill C-13\">{{cite web | url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2014/05/13/amanda_todds_mother_raises_concerns_about_cyberbullying_bill.html | title=Amanda Todd's mother raises concerns about cyberbullying bill: Families of cyberbullying victims want legislation, but some have concerns about warrantless access to Canadians personal data. | publisher=www.thestar.com | date=2014-04-13 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Boutilier, Alex | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028011059/https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2014/05/13/amanda_todds_mother_raises_concerns_about_cyberbullying_bill.html | archivedate=October 28, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref name=\" Justice Committee on May 13th, 2014\">{{cite web | url=https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/ | title=Carol Todd's Testimony regarding Bill C-13 | publisher=www.openparliament.ca | date=2014-05-14 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Todd, Carol | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918140017/https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/ | archivedate=September 18, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The definition of cyberbullying itself has been a matter of considerable debate,<ref name=\" Cyberbullying creating difficult questions for legal system\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/cyberbullying-law-1.3442677 | title=Cyberbullying creating difficult questions for legal system: Victims' advocates calling for new cyberbullying laws, but pinning down broad term difficult | publisher=CBCNEWS | date=2016-02-29 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Quigley, Joseph | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924081034/http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/cyberbullying-law-1.3442677 | archivedate=September 24, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> as have the bill's privacy provisions (particularly in regard to [[encryption]] technologies).<ref name=\"Apple's encryption battle with the FBI could spill into Canada\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/apple-encryption-privacy-security-1.3452630 | title=Apple's encryption battle with the FBI could spill into Canada: U.S. legal fight will be closely watched north of the border | publisher=CBC News | date=2016-02-19 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Powers, Lucas | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027234946/http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/apple-encryption-privacy-security-1.3452630 | archivedate=October 27, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> It went into effect on March 9, 2015.<ref name=\"Bill C-13 Goes Into Effect\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/anti-cyberbullying-law-bill-c-13-now-in-effect-1.2270460 | title=Anti-cyberbullying law, Bill C-13, now in effect | publisher=ctvnews.ca/ | date=2015-03-09 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Puzic, Sonja | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920192357/http://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/anti-cyberbullying-law-bill-c-13-now-in-effect-1.2270460 | archivedate=September 20, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> It had largely been promoted as protecting minors, but applies to all ages.<ref name=\"Canada\u2019s cyberbullying and revenge porn law applies to adults too\">{{cite web | url=http://www.rcinet.ca/en/2015/04/30/canadas-cyberbullying-and-revenge-porn-law-applies-to-adults-too/ | title=Canada's cyberbullying and revenge porn law applies to adults too | publisher=Radio Canada International | date=2016-04-30 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Montgomery, Mark | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912032420/http://www.rcinet.ca/en/2015/04/30/canadas-cyberbullying-and-revenge-porn-law-applies-to-adults-too/ | archivedate=September 12, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cyberstalking legislation]]\n* [[Harassment by computer]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Internet|Free speech|Society|Human sexuality|Canada|Politics}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://amandatoddlegacy.org/ Amanda Todd Legacy] \u2013 Official website administered by Todd's family\n* {{youtube|vOHXGNx-E7E|''My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm''}}\n* [http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU Transcript of YouTube video]\n* [http://prezi.com/atoa68wrotkm/cyber-bulling/ ''Cyber Bullying'']: a [[Prezi]] Todd made about cyberbullying one month before her death\n*{{cite serial|title=The Sextortion of Amanda Todd|episode= |url= http://www.cbc.ca/fifth/episodes/2013-2014/the-sextortion-of-amanda-todd|series=[[The Fifth Estate (TV)|The Fifth Estate]]|network=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=15 November 2013|season=39|number=|minutes=}}\n*{{IMDb name|5331599|Amanda Todd}}\n* {{findagrave|128393627|Amanda Todd}}\n* [https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/only/ Carol Todd's oral testimony regarding Bill C-13]\n* [https://openparliament.ca/bills/41-2/C-13/ English text of Bill C-13]\n* [https://needhelpnow.ca/app/en/ ''Need Help Now'': Resources for subjects of self/peer sexual exploitation incidents]\n\n{{Bullying}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Todd, Amanda, suicide of}}\n[[Category:2012 in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Bullying and suicide]]\n[[Category:Deaths by person]]\n[[Category:Sexuality and computing]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-move-indef}}\n{{pp-semi-indef}}\n{{Use Canadian English|date=November 2018}}\n{{short description|suicide of a Canadian student that took place on October 10, 2012}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2013}}\n{{Infobox event\n| image                    = AmandaToddVideo.jpg\n| image_alt                = A girl in her mid-teens holding a cut-out piece of paper or card with the words \"I have nobody, I need someone\" and a sad emoticon written on it.\n| caption                  = A screenshot of Todd's YouTube video\n| date                     = {{start date|2012|10|10}}\n| location                 = [[Port Coquitlam]], British Columbia, Canada\n| cause                    = Hanging\n| inquest                  = British Columbia Coroners Service\n| coroner                  = Barb McLintock<ref name=\"Fox\">{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/|title=Canadian teen found dead weeks after posting wrenching YouTube video detailing bullying|date=October 12, 2012|accessdate=April 21, 2013|work=Fox News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130607165008/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/|archivedate=June 7, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n| suspects                 = Aydin Coban<ref name= \"CBC Coyban\"/>\n| charges                  = Indecent assault and child pornography (Netherlands)<ref name=\"Suspect\">[https://web.archive.org/web/20140421074026/http://news.msn.com/crime-justice/dutch-mans-case-linked-to-amanda-todd Dutch man's case linked to Amanda Todd], ''MSN.com'', 18 April 2014, Hainsworth, J., Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref>\n}}\n'''Amanda Michelle Todd''' (November 27, 1996 \u2013 October 10, 2012)<ref>{{cite news|last1=Cahute|first1=Larissa|title=Amanda Todd: Hundreds hear tributes from family, friends, teachers|url=https://theprovince.com/news/Amanda+Todd+Hundreds+hear+tributes+from+family+friends+teachers/7568025/story.html|accessdate=November 13, 2016|work=[[The Province]]|date=November 19, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121120112208/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Amanda+Todd+Hundreds+hear+tributes+from+family+friends+teachers/7568025/story.html|archivedate=November 20, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Martins|first1=Monisha|title=Amanda Todd celebrated in 'the birthday party she wanted'|url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/179887911.html|accessdate=November 13, 2016|work=[[Tri-City News]]|date=November 18, 2012|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121216054345/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/179887911.html|archivedate=December 16, 2012}}</ref> was a 15-year-old Canadian student and victim of [[cyberbullying]] who [[suicide by hanging|hanged herself]] at her home in [[Port Coquitlam]], a city in the province of [[British Columbia]], [[Canada]]. Before her death, Todd posted a video on [[YouTube]] in which she used a series of flash cards to tell her experience of being blackmailed into exposing her breasts via webcam,<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> and of being bullied and physically assaulted. The video went [[Viral video|viral]] after her death,<ref name=\"cbccareport\">{{cite news |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/story/2012/11/18/bc-amanda-todd-celebration-of-life.html |title=Amanda Todd tribute honours life of bullied teen |place=Calgary, CA |publisher=[[CBC.ca|CBC]] |work=News |date=November 18, 2012 |accessdate=November 24, 2012 |quote=After she died, the video gained worldwide recognition and registered more than six million hits, and copies of the video re-posted to YouTube have since gained at least 16 million additional hits. |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121121030651/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/calgary/story/2012/11/18/bc-amanda-todd-celebration-of-life.html |archivedate=November 21, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> resulting in international media attention. The video has had more than 13 million views as of October 2019.<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> The [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] and British Columbia Coroners Service launched investigations into the suicide.\n\nIn response to her death, [[Christy Clark]], the [[Premier of British Columbia]], made an online statement of condolence and suggested a national discussion on criminalizing [[cyberbullying]].<ref>{{cite news|title=RCMP launch investigation into death of bullied BC teen|place=CA|url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/rcmp-launch-investigation-into-death-of-bullied-b-c-teen-1.993029|accessdate=October 13, 2012|newspaper=CTV News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121013030309/http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/rcmp-launch-investigation-into-death-of-bullied-b-c-teen-1.993029|archivedate=October 13, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=After Amanda Todd's death, Christy Clark says new laws may be needed to combat bullying|url=https://vancouversun.com/life/After+Amanda+Todd+death+Christy+Clark+says+laws+needed+combat/7384108/story.html|publisher=Vancouver Sun|accessdate=October 13, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015002318/http://www.vancouversun.com/life/After+Amanda+Todd+death+Christy+Clark+says+laws+needed+combat/7384108/story.html|archivedate=October 15, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 24, 2001}}</ref> Also, a motion was introduced in the Canadian House of Commons to propose a study of the scope of bullying in Canada, and for more funding and support for anti-bullying organizations. Todd's mother Carol established the Amanda Todd Trust, receiving donations to support anti-bullying awareness education and programs for young people with mental health problems.\n\n==Background and suicide==\nOn September 7, 2012, Todd posted a 9-minute [[YouTube]] video titled ''My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm'', which showed her using a series of [[flashcards]] to tell of her experiences being bullied.<ref name=\"Video\">{{YouTube|vOHXGNx-E7E|My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm}}, 7 September 2012, Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref> The video went viral after her death on October 10, 2012, receiving over 1,600,000 views by October 13, 2012,<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tormenters-target-b-c-teen-amanda-todd-s-online-memorials-1.994594 |title=Online bullying of B.C. teen continues amid police probe &#124; CTV News |publisher=Ctvnews.ca |date=October 13, 2012 |accessdate=October 14, 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190713125954/https://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/tormenters-target-amanda-todd-s-online-memorials-amid-police-probe-1.994594 |archive-date=July 13, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> with news websites from around the world linking to it.\n[[File:Amanda Todd - 01.jpg|thumb|left|Facebook photo of Todd]]\n\nDuring the video, Todd writes that when she was in grade 7 (2009\u201310), around the same time she moved in with her father,<ref name=\"VancouverSun\" /> she used [[video chat]] to meet new people over the Internet and received compliments on her looks.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\">[http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU Amanda Todd - Transcript of video] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121210215745/http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU |date=December 10, 2012 }}, ''Pastebin.com'', 15 October 2012, Huntley, R., Retrieved 18 April 2014.</ref> A stranger convinced Todd to bare her breasts on camera (an exploitative phenomenon known as \"capping\", short for [[screen shot|screen capturing]]),<ref name=\"Capping\">{{cite web | url=http://www.mapleridgenews.com/breaking_news/175880591.html | title=Predators lurk behind computer screens | publisher=Maple Ridge News | author=Martins, Monisha | accessdate=2016-09-13 | date=2016-10-26 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160926201721/http://www.mapleridgenews.com/breaking_news/175880591.html | archivedate=September 26, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> after attempting to do so for a year.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> He later blackmailed her by threatening to give the topless photo to her friends unless she gave him a \"show\";<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\">{{cite news |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/10/12/world/americas/canada-teen-bullying/index.html?iref=allsearch |title=Bullied Canadian teen leaves behind chilling YouTube video \u2013 CNN.com |publisher=Edition.cnn.com |date=October 13, 2012 |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121026003136/http://edition.cnn.com/2012/10/12/world/americas/canada-teen-bullying/index.html?iref=allsearch |archivedate=October 26, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> she also featured briefly on the faux animated news show ''Daily Capper'' on BlogTV  in an incident that attracted the vigilante attentions of the group [[Anonymous (group)|Anonymous]] after her suicide.<ref name=\"Daily Capper\">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailydot.com/society/sick-pedophile-ring-blackmail-amanda-todd/|title=Inside the sick pedophile ring that blackmailed girls like Amanda Todd|last=Morris|first=Kevin|date=2012-10-19|website=The Daily Dot|publisher=|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160817110141/http://www.dailydot.com/society/sick-pedophile-ring-blackmail-amanda-todd/|archivedate=August 17, 2016|url-status=live|accessdate=2016-09-15|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Anonymous, Daily Capper, and Kody1206\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/in-the-darkest-corners-of-the-internet-bullies-and-predators-hide-in-plain-sight/article4650771/ | title=In the darkest corners of the Internet, bullies and predators hide in plain sight | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2012-10-25 | accessdate=2016-09-15 | author=Woo, Andrea | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161010084738/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/in-the-darkest-corners-of-the-internet-bullies-and-predators-hide-in-plain-sight/article4650771/ | archivedate=October 10, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> An episode of ''Daily Capper'' that attempted to take the moral high ground, very different in tone from their usual material, was released a month after her death.<ref name=\"The Suspicious Return of the Daily Capper\">{{cite web | url=https://www.vice.com/en_ca/read/the-suspicious-return-of-the-daily-capper | title=The Suspicious Return of the Daily Capper | publisher=Vice | date=2012-11-12 | accessdate=2016-09-15 | author=McGuire, Patrick | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160505095940/http://www.vice.com/en_ca/read/the-suspicious-return-of-the-daily-capper | archivedate=May 5, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nTodd wrote that during the Christmas 2010 break, police informed her at 4:00&nbsp;a.m. that the photo was circulating on the Internet.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> She wrote that she experienced [[anxiety]], [[depression (mood)|depression]], and [[panic disorder]] due to having been sexually exploited online and cyberbullied.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Her family moved to a new home, where Todd later said she began using alcohol and other drugs.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\" />\n\nA year later, Todd's blackmailer reappeared, creating a [[Facebook]] profile that used the topless photo as its profile image and contacting classmates at her new school.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Again, Todd was teased, eventually changing schools for a second time.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> She wrote that she began chatting to \"an old guy friend\" who contacted her.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> The friend invited Todd to his house, where they had sex while his girlfriend was on holiday.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Villalva|first=Brittney R.|title=Amanda Todd: 15-Year-Old Tells Story of Bullying and Suicide Before Death|url=http://global.christianpost.com/news/amanda-todd-15-year-old-tells-story-of-bullying-and-suicide-before-death-video-83253/|work=The Christian Post|accessdate=October 16, 2012|date=October 14, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130102192909/http://global.christianpost.com/news/amanda-todd-15-year-old-tells-story-of-bullying-and-suicide-before-death-video-83253/|archivedate=January 2, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The following week, the boy's girlfriend and a group of about 15 others confronted Todd at school, shouting insults, with the boy's girlfriend punching her;<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Todd fell to the ground, then lay in a ditch, where her father found her.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> After the attack, Todd attempted suicide by drinking bleach, but survived after being rushed to hospital to have her stomach pumped.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref name=\"CNNVideo\" /> \"It killed me inside and I thought I was gonna actully{{sic}} die\", Todd commented in her video.<ref name=\"Fox\" /><ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" />\n\nAfter returning home, Todd discovered abusive messages about her suicide attempt posted to Facebook.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> In March, 2012, her family moved to another city to start afresh, but Todd was unable to escape the past.<ref name=\"Video\" /><ref name=\"Transcript\" /> According to her mother, \"Every time she moved schools he would go undercover and become a Facebook friend. What the guy did was he went online to the kids who went to [the new school] and said that he was going to be a new student \u2014 that he was starting school the following week and that he wanted some friends and could they friend him on Facebook. He eventually gathered people's names and sent Todd's video to her new school\", including students, teachers and parents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://vancouversun.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7384521/story.html|title=Amanda Todd's mother speaks out about her daughter, bullying (with video)|author=Gillian Shaw|date=October 14, 2012|work=Vancouver Sun|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131031121155/http://www.vancouversun.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7384521/story.html|archivedate=October 31, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Six months later, further messages and abuse were still being posted to social networking sites. With Todd's mental state worsening, she began to engage in [[Self-harm|self-mutilation]] and cutting.<ref name=\"Transcript\" /> Despite taking her prescribed antidepressants and receiving counseling, she overdosed and was hospitalized for two days.<ref name=\"Transcript\" /><ref>{{cite news|last=Keneally|first=Meghan|title=Tragedy as girl, 15, kills herself just one month after posting desperate YouTube plea begging bullies to stop tormenting her|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2216543/Amanda-Todd-Canadian-teen-kills-desperate-video-plea-begging-bullies-stop.html|publisher=Daily Mail|accessdate=October 13, 2012|location=London|date=October 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20121013084629/http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2216543/Amanda-Todd-Canadian-teen-kills-desperate-video-plea-begging-bullies-stop.html|archivedate=October 13, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nTodd was taunted by other students at her school for her low grades, a consequence of a [[language-based learning disability]], and for the time she spent in hospital to treat her severe depression.<ref name=\"VancouverSun\">{{cite news|last=Shaw|first=Gillian|title='She shared everything with me': Amanda Todd's mother talks about her life with her daughter|url=https://vancouversun.com/health/shared+everything+with+Amanda+Todd+mother+talks+about+life/7419475/story.html|accessdate=October 21, 2012|newspaper=vancouversun.com|date=October 20, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121022210457/http://www.vancouversun.com/health/shared+everything+with+Amanda+Todd+mother+talks+about+life/7419475/story.html|archivedate=October 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> \"It didn't really help that after she got out of the hospital recently some kids started calling her 'psycho' and saying she had been in the crazy hospital,\" her mother said. \"She went to the hospital, she had therapy, she had counseling, she was on a good track. On the day she gets out, that happens. I shake my head and I think, 'Are kids really that nasty, do they really not think, what if it was them?'\"<ref name=\"VancouverSun\" />\n\nOn October 10, 2012, at about 6:00&nbsp;PM ([[Pacific Daylight Time|PDT]]), Todd was found hanging at her home.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/amanda-todd-suicide-girls-mum-1379909|title=Amanda Todd: Suicide girl's mum reveals more harrowing details of cyber bullying campaign that drove her daughter to her death|last=Bleaney|first=Rob|date=2012-10-15|work=mirror|access-date=2018-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180623034852/https://www.mirror.co.uk/news/world-news/amanda-todd-suicide-girls-mum-1379909|archive-date=June 23, 2018|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Port Coquitlam teen driven to death by cyberbullying (with video)|url=https://montrealgazette.com/technology/Port+Coquitlam+teen+driven+death+cyberbullying+with+video/7375941/story.html|accessdate=October 15, 2012|newspaper=Vancouver Sun|date=October 12, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015020557/http://www.montrealgazette.com/technology/Port+Coquitlam+teen+driven+death+cyberbullying+with+video/7375941/story.html|archivedate=October 15, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> At the time of her death, Todd was a [[Tenth grade|grade 10]] student<ref name=\"washingtonpost1\">{{cite news |agency=Associated Press |url=http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/ |title=Canadian teen found dead weeks after posting wrenching YouTube video detailing bullying |publisher=Fox News |date=2012-10-12 |accessdate=October 31, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121031180509/http://www.foxnews.com/world/2012/10/12/canadian-teen-found-dead-weeks-after-posting-wrenching-youtube-video-detailing/ |archivedate=October 31, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> at CABE Secondary in Coquitlam,<ref>{{cite web |last=Luymes |first=Glenda |url=https://theprovince.com/news/Cyberbullying+Amanda+Todd+suicide+prompts+grief/7376942/story.html |title=Cyberbullying: Outpouring of grief over teen's suicide (with video) |publisher=The province |date=March 25, 2002 |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121014091826/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Cyberbullying+Amanda+Todd+suicide+prompts+grief/7376942/story.html |archivedate=October 14, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> a school that caters to students who have experienced social and behaviour issues in previous educational settings.<ref>{{cite web | title = About CABE | url = http://www.sd43.bc.ca/secondary/CABE/About/Pages/ | publisher = sd43 | accessdate = November 5, 2012 | location = BC, CA }}{{Dead link|date=October 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n== Investigation, arrest and conviction ==\n\nA preliminary investigation by British Columbia Coroners Service showed that Todd's death was a suicide. The cause of death was reported in some media as hanging,<ref name=\"Penny\">{{cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/its-too-late-for-amanda-todd-but-we-must-out-the-cyberbullies-8217004.html|title=It's too late for Amanda Todd, but we must out the cyber-bullies \u2013 Comment \u2013 Voices \u2013 The Independent|last=Penny|first=Laurie|date=October 18, 2012|work=[[The Independent]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, a 15-year-old Canadian schoolgirl hanged herself, last week, after years of unrelenting abuse by peers and online predators, one of whom persuaded her to flash her breasts and then shared the picture around the world.|location=London|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122145733/http://www.independent.co.uk/voices/comment/its-too-late-for-amanda-todd-but-we-must-out-the-cyberbullies-8217004.html|archivedate=November 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Agomuoh\">{{cite news|url=http://www.ibtimes.com/amanda-todd-suicide-doesnt-end-cyber-torment-ridiculed-teen-846827|title=Amanda Todd Suicide Doesn't End Cyber Torment For Ridiculed Teen|last=Agomuoh|first=Fionna|date=October 15, 2012|work=[[International Business Times]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd of British Columbia apparently hanged herself on Oct. 10 after a grave mistake followed her for the rest of her brief life.|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130316173856/http://www.ibtimes.com/amanda-todd-suicide-doesnt-end-cyber-torment-ridiculed-teen-846827|archivedate=March 16, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Ryall\">{{cite news|url=http://www.news.com.au/world/online-bully-victim-amanda-todd-still-tormented-in-death/story-fndir2ev-1226497411838|title=Anonymous outs bully they claim drove Amanda Todd to suicide, mum says leave her family alone &#124;News.com.au|last=Ryall|first=Jenni|date=October 17, 2012|work=[[News Limited]]|accessdate=November 20, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, from Vancouver, British Columbia, Canada, was found hanged in her home on October 10, weeks after she uploaded a video to YouTube that describes \u2013 via a series of note cards \u2013 her treatment at the hands of a cyber bully.|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121114052415/http://www.news.com.au/world/online-bully-victim-amanda-todd-still-tormented-in-death/story-fndir2ev-1226497411838|archivedate=November 14, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"Dufour\">{{cite news|last=Dufour|first=Katinka|title=Amanda Todd case highlights issue of online bullying|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9612030/Amanda-Todd-case-highlights-issue-of-online-bullying.html|accessdate=November 11, 2012|newspaper=telegraph.co.uk|date=October 16, 2012|quote=Amanda Todd, was found hanged in her home in Port Coquitlam, British Columbia, Canada, last Wednesday, one month before her 16th birthday.|location=London|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121018195156/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9612030/Amanda-Todd-case-highlights-issue-of-online-bullying.html|archivedate=October 18, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> but the exact cause of death had not been released.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd was not internet obsessed, mother says|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/amanda-todd-was-not-internet-obsessed-mother-says-1.1190867|publisher=CBC News|accessdate=May 25, 2014|date=October 23, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140525202706/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/amanda-todd-was-not-internet-obsessed-mother-says-1.1190867|archivedate=May 25, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Royal Canadian Mounted Police]] (RCMP) and British Columbia Coroners Service put 20 full-time investigators on the case.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> The Coquitlam and Ridge Meadows serious crime teams cooperated in a full investigation, conducting interviews and examining factors that may have contributed to Todd's death.<ref name=\"globaltvbc.com\">{{cite web |url=http://www.globaltvbc.com/rcmp+launch+full+investigation+into+amanda+todds+death/6442732749/story.html |title=Global BC &#124; RCMP launch full investigation into Amanda Todd's death |publisher=Globaltvbc.com |date= |accessdate=October 13, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121015023057/http://www.globaltvbc.com/rcmp+launch+full+investigation+into+amanda+todds+death/6442732749/story.html |archivedate=October 15, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> Investigators are reviewing content at social media sites and actively monitoring pages.<ref name=\"globaltvbc.com\" />\n\nThe Canadian national organization [[Cybertip.ca]] reported having received a tip about Todd nearly a year before her suicide. The anti-child-exploitation group stated that, in November 2011, a concerned citizen reported that images of Todd were in circulation on the Internet. That information was provided to law enforcement as well as child welfare agencies.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\">[http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/15/bc-amanda-todd-tormentor-anonymous.html Amanda Todd's alleged tormentor named by hacker group - British Columbia - CBC News] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016104520/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/15/bc-amanda-todd-tormentor-anonymous.html |date=October 16, 2012 }}</ref> According to the CBC news program ''[[The Fifth Estate (TV)|The Fifth Estate]]'', the RCMP were repeatedly informed that the juvenile was being sexually extorted by an adult male, and in response the RCMP told the family there was \"nothing that could be done\" about it.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suicide-rcmp-repeatedly-told-of-blackmailer-s-attempts-1.2427097|title=Amanda Todd suicide: RCMP repeatedly told of blackmailer's attempts|date=15 November 2013|accessdate=19 April 2014|work=CBC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217180217/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suicide-rcmp-repeatedly-told-of-blackmailer-s-attempts-1.2427097|archivedate=February 17, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> According to the Ontario Provincial Police (OPP), however, the crime of \"sextortion\" can be investigated quite successfully.{{Citation needed|date=January 2019}}\n\nFollowing an investigation by [[Facebook]]'s security unit, whose report was forwarded by U.S. authorities to the [[Child Exploitation and Online Protection Centre]] attached to the British [[National Crime Agency]],<ref name=\"Facebook security unit.\">{{cite news | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/on-the-trail-of-amanda-todds-alleged-tormentor/article18935075/?page=all | title=On the trail of Amanda Todd's alleged tormentor | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2014-05-31 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=White, Patrick | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170129024135/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/on-the-trail-of-amanda-todds-alleged-tormentor/article18935075/?page=all | archivedate=January 29, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and then to Dutch authorities, in January 2014 Dutch police arrested a man in a case involving multiple victims in the Netherlands, U.K., and Canada, having installed [[spyware]] on his computers; \"chilling\" chat logs of extortion, numerous images of child pornography, and 5,800 bookmarked names that served as a database of potential victims and their social networks were found.<ref name=\"De Visser\">{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/16/15-year-old-amanda-todd-s-alleged-sextortionist-on-trial-at-last.html |title=Sextortion 15-Year-Old Amanda Todd's Alleged Sextortionist on Trial at Last |last=De Visser |first=Nadette |date=February 16, 2017 |newspaper=[[The Daily Beast]] |access-date=March 10, 2017 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170312072158/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/02/16/15-year-old-amanda-todd-s-alleged-sextortionist-on-trial-at-last.html |archivedate=March 12, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In April 2014, it was reported that Dutch authorities charged a 35-year-old man of dual Dutch and Turkish citizenship (identified only as \"Aydin C.\" within the Netherlands<ref name=\"Suspect\" /><ref>[http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/who-is-the-dutch-man-arrested-in-connection-with-the-death-of-amanda-todd-1.1781755 Who is the Dutch man arrested in connection with the death of Amanda Todd?] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140901183951/http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/who-is-the-dutch-man-arrested-in-connection-with-the-death-of-amanda-todd-1.1781755 |date=September 1, 2014 }}, [[CTV News]], April 18, 2014</ref> in accordance with Dutch privacy laws) with indecent assault and child pornography.<ref name=\"Suspect\" /> That same month, the RCMP announced that the man had been charged with extortion, internet luring, criminal harassment and possession and distribution of child pornography for his alleged offenses against Todd and other child victims, both male and female.<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/news/story/1.2614034 | work=CBC News | title=Amanda Todd case: RCMP detail 5 charges against Dutch citizen | url-status=dead | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419101916/http://www.cbc.ca/m/touch/news/story/1.2614034 | archivedate=April 19, 2014 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Todd's mother thanked police, but also said that she believed more than one person was involved.<ref>{{cite news|website=BBC|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27076991|title=Man charged in Netherlands in Amanda Todd suicide case|date=18 April 2014|accessdate=18 April 2014|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419022314/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-27076991|archivedate=April 19, 2014|df=mdy-all}}</ref> On 28 January 2015, [[CBC News]] said that Aydin Coban had written an open letter proclaiming his innocence.<ref name=\"CBC Coyban\">{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd suspect Aydin Coban writes open letter proclaiming innocence|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suspect-aydin-coban-writes-open-letter-proclaiming-innocence-1.2935055|website=cbc.ca|publisher=[[CBC News]]|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150709235902/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/amanda-todd-suspect-aydin-coban-writes-open-letter-proclaiming-innocence-1.2935055|archivedate=July 9, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nDutch authorities dropped some child pornography charges in October 2015;<ref name=\"Netherlands drops child porn charges against man also accused in Amanda Todd case\">{{cite web | url=https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2015/10/27/netherlands-drops-child-porn-charges-in-amanda-todd-case.html | title=Netherlands drops child porn charges against man also accused in Amanda Todd case Dutch prosecutor has dropped child pornography charges that relate to accused's alleged non-Dutch victims, suspect's lawyer says. | publisher=thestar.com | date=2015-10-27 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Kestler-D\u2019Amours, Jillian | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320091549/https://www.thestar.com/news/world/2015/10/27/netherlands-drops-child-porn-charges-in-amanda-todd-case.html | archivedate=March 20, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref name=\"Extradition to proceed in Amanda Todd case\">{{cite web | url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/extradition-to-proceed-in-amanda-todd-case-1.2096989 | title=Extradition to proceed in Amanda Todd case: Decision by Dutch authorities to leave the Todd case out of legal proceedings not expected to affect court case here regarding Port Coquitlam teen. | publisher=Tri-City News | date=2015-10-27 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Strandberg, Diane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919074553/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/extradition-to-proceed-in-amanda-todd-case-1.2096989 | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Coban's case went to trial in February 2017, and concluded on March 16, 2017. He faced 72 charges of sexual assault and extortion in the Netherlands involving 39 alleged victims (34 young women and five men in countries as various as Britain, Canada, Norway and the United States, some of whom had been harassed for years); eventually convicted and sentenced on the Dutch charges of internet fraud and blackmail, he faces five separate Canadian charges related to Todd (herself not one of the 39), and it was anticipated that he would be [[extradition|extradited]] to Canada no sooner than the middle of 2018 whilst serving his Dutch sentence of 10 years and 8 months. Carol Todd expressed relief at the sentence.<ref name=\"De Visser\"/><ref name=\"Dutch Coban Trial\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39295474 |title=Amanda Todd case: Accused Dutch man jailed for cyberbullying |date=2017-03-16 |website=BBC |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170317084824/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39295474 |archivedate=March 17, 2017 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> In December 2019, it was reported that Canadian authorities were preparing for the extradition.<ref>https://globalnews.ca/news/6323357/potential-extradition-amanda-todd-accused-tormentor/</ref>\n\n==Reaction==\nTodd's suicide received widespread international media coverage, much of which included a link to her YouTube video and an email address provided by the RCMP appealing for information from the public. Within 24 hours of the appeal, over 400 tips were received.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> The RCMP has stated that its investigation was hindered by the amount of false information in online postings after Todd's death, and by scams claiming to raise money for her family.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/16/bc-amanda-todd-scam-websites.html|title=Amanda Todd probe delayed by online rumours, scams|publisher=CBC.ca|author=Alan Waterman, Canadian Press|date=October 17, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019000816/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/story/2012/10/16/bc-amanda-todd-scam-websites.html|archivedate=October 19, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 19, 2012, a series of vigils was held across Canada and internationally to remember Todd and other victims of bullying.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/10/18/toronto-bullying-silence.html|title=Bullying victims remembered in vigils worldwide:Vigils, memorials follow suicide of B.C. teen Amanda Todd last week|publisher=CBC.ca|date=October 19, 2012|accessdate=October 19, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121020004820/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/story/2012/10/18/toronto-bullying-silence.html|archivedate=October 20, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> A [[minute of silence]] was observed by a quarter of a million students in the [[Toronto District School Board]] district.<ref>{{cite news|last=Brown|first=Louise|title=Amanda Todd: Toronto students to remember bullied teen who committed suicide|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1273960--amanda-todd-toronto-students-to-remember-bullied-teen-who-committed-suicide|accessdate=October 20, 2012|newspaper=Toronto Star|date=October 18, 2012|location=Toronto ON|page=2|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021011923/http://www.thestar.com/news/gta/article/1273960--amanda-todd-toronto-students-to-remember-bullied-teen-who-committed-suicide|archivedate=October 21, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref> The same day, Todd's mother was a guest of the 2012 [[We Day]] event in Vancouver, a week after Todd's death. Bullying had been scheduled as a topic before Todd's death and was addressed by speakers [[Magic Johnson]], musician and anti-bullying advocate [[Demi Lovato]] and British Columbia Premier [[Christy Clark]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://theprovince.com/news/Premier+tells+kids+stand+change+against+bullying/7410549/story.html |title=Amanda Todd's death felt at We Day event in Vancouver |publisher=The Province |date=October 19, 2012 |author=James Keller, Canadian Press |accessdate=October 19, 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121019141549/http://www.theprovince.com/news/Premier+tells+kids+stand+change+against+bullying/7410549/story.html |archivedate=October 19, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nInitially, Todd's mother was denied entry to an anti-bullying conference for fear that her presence would upset other attendees.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ferreras|first=Jesse|title=Amanda Todd's Mother, Carol Todd, Excluded From Anti-Bullying Conference|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/14/carol-todd-amanda-todd-mother-anti-bullying-conference_n_2130424.html|work=Huffpost British Columbia|publisher=HPMG News|accessdate=November 18, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121118040209/http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/14/carol-todd-amanda-todd-mother-anti-bullying-conference_n_2130424.html|archivedate=November 18, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 14, 2012}}</ref> The family was invited to attend later events.<ref>{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd Memorial Set For Sunday|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/17/amanda-todd-memorial_n_2151479.html|work=Huffpost British Columbia|publisher=HPMG News|accessdate=November 18, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119010742/http://www.huffingtonpost.ca/2012/11/17/amanda-todd-memorial_n_2151479.html|archivedate=November 19, 2012|df=mdy-all|date=November 17, 2012}}</ref>\n\nOn November 18, 2012, 600 people gathered at a final farewell ceremony for Todd at [[Red Robinson Show Theatre]] in Coquitlam, near her home. Carol Todd told the gathering that her daughter had left behind \"a larger-than-life message that has sparked the world and has made it open its eyes, its ears and its hearts\".<ref>[https://vancouversun.com/life/Amanda+Todd+honoured+hundreds+Coquitlam+memorial+service/7567970/story.html Amanda Todd honoured by hundreds at Coquitlam memorial service] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121122000957/http://www.vancouversun.com/life/Amanda+Todd+honoured+hundreds+Coquitlam+memorial+service/7567970/story.html |date=November 22, 2012 }} Retrieved Nov 19, 2012</ref>\n\nInternet hacking and activist group [[Anonymous (group)|Anonymous]] alleged that a 32-year-old man was Todd's blackmailer and main tormentor. The group published the [[Vancouver]]-area man's name and address on the Internet, resulting in the man's receipt of online threats of vigilante justice.<ref name=\"autogenerated1\" /> After investigating the tip, police determined that the allegations were unfounded, and said that \"false information that is being spread by people who appear to be trying to use Amanda's story to do harm or make a profit\" was one of the challenges they faced.<ref name=\"ottawacitizen\">{{Cite journal|last1=Shaw|last2=Sinoski|first1=Gillian|first2=Kelly|title=B.C. man denies harassing Amanda Todd; RCMP say allegations are 'unfounded'|journal=[[Ottawa Citizen]]|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/news/denies+harassing+Amanda+Todd+RCMP+allegations+unfounded/7400309/story.html|publisher=Postmedia Network Inc.|date=October 17, 2012|accessdate=January 27, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121021230743/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/news/denies+harassing+Amanda+Todd+RCMP+allegations+unfounded/7400309/story.html|archivedate=October 21, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nAccording to an interview with the ''[[The Vancouver Sun|Vancouver Sun]]'', the publication of his identity on social media sites resulted in over 50 emails and thousands of Facebook death threats.<ref name=\"ottawacitizen\" /> A member of Anonymous had attempted to dissuade the group from publishing the information, saying that they had the right person but that the address belonged to someone else, not the target. ''[[Slate (magazine)|Slate]]'' reported that the person who was responsible turned out to be 19, not 32.<ref name=\"inqtodd\">{{cite web|title=Amanda Todd Investigation: Police Say Anonymous Outed the Wrong Man|url=http://www.inquisitr.com/367540/amanda-todd-investigation-police-say-anonymous-outed-the-wrong-man/|publisher=inquisitr.com|accessdate=December 23, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121225005441/http://www.inquisitr.com/367540/amanda-todd-investigation-police-say-anonymous-outed-the-wrong-man/|archivedate=December 25, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"globewoo\">{{cite news|last=Woo|first=Andrea|title='Hacktivist' group names second person in Amanda Todd case|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/hacktivist-group-names-second-person-in-amanda-todd-case/article4619867/|accessdate=December 23, 2012|newspaper=The Globe and Mail|date=October 17, 2012|location=Toronto|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121222190944/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/british-columbia/hacktivist-group-names-second-person-in-amanda-todd-case/article4619867/|archivedate=December 22, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\n=== Mainstream media ===\nMichelle Dean of ''[[The New Yorker]]'' compared Todd's death to the [[suicide of Tyler Clementi]], an [[LGBT]] student at [[Rutgers University]] who jumped to his death from the [[George Washington Bridge]] after his roommate encouraged friends to watch a live stream of Clementi kissing another man. In an early piece questioning the assumptions of perpetrators of [[nonconsensual pornography]], she quotes [[Mary Anne Franks]]:{{quote|Women have become, as Franks put it, \"unwilling avatars\", unable to control their own images online, and then told to put up with it for the sake of \"freedom\", for the good of the community. And then they are incorrectly told, even if the public is behind them, that they have no remedies in the law. They are shouted down by people with a view of freedom of speech more literal than that held by any judge.}}\nand concludes:<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dean|first1=Michelle|title=The Story of Amanda Todd|url=https://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/the-story-of-amanda-todd|website=newyorker.com|publisher=[[The New Yorker]]|year=2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150713103045/http://www.newyorker.com/culture/culture-desk/the-story-of-amanda-todd|archivedate=July 13, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref>{{quote|...[But] whatever Amanda Todd might have been thinking, whatever else might be true, she did get one thing out of this: Amanda Todd did manage to, just once, tell her own story. She got to drown out the version of her that strangers had put out on the Web. It's a small comfort. But it was perhaps the only one she had left.}}\n\n''[[Vancouver Magazine]]'' titled a piece on Todd \"The Girl Who Woke Up the World\"; in 2012 she was the third-most [[Google]]d person, and by 2013 vigils had been held in 38 countries. Her mother continues to be the subject of cyber-stalking.<ref name=\"The Girl Who Woke Up The World\">{{cite web | url=http://vanmag.com/uncategorized/the-girl-who-woke-up-the-world-amanda-todd/ | title=The Girl Who Woke Up The World: Amanda Todd | publisher=Vancouver Magazine | date=2016-10-01 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170503011657/http://vanmag.com/uncategorized/the-girl-who-woke-up-the-world-amanda-todd/ | archivedate=May 3, 2017 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Social media===\nAfter Todd's suicide, more than one million Facebook users \"liked\" her Facebook memorial page.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /><ref>{{cite web|last=Hewlett|first=Jason|title=Amanda Todd video put spotlight on bullying|url=http://www.kamloopsnews.ca/article/20130103/KAMLOOPS0101/121239984/-1/kamloops/story-of-the-year-amanda-todd-video-put-spotlight-on-bullying|work=kamloopsnews.ca|accessdate=April 12, 2013|date=January 3, 2013|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130517033216/http://www.kamloopsnews.ca/article/20130103/KAMLOOPS0101/121239984/-1/kamloops/story-of-the-year-amanda-todd-video-put-spotlight-on-bullying|archivedate=May 17, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> Mingled among the positive support and comments are attacks and images from strangers and people claiming to be her former classmates.<ref name=\"ctvnews.ca\" /> After one man's derogatory Facebook comments about Todd's death were reported to his employer, the [[Grafton-Fraser]] Mr. Big & Tall clothing chain, it confirmed that he was no longer an employee.<ref>{{cite news|title=Ontario man loses job after writing cruel Facebook comment about Amanda Todd|url=http://news.nationalpost.com/2012/10/17/cruel-facebook-comment-about-amanda-todds-suicide-costs-man-his-job/|accessdate=November 4, 2012|newspaper=National Post Wire Services|date=Oct 17, 2012|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://wayback.archive-it.org/all/20121018183355/http://news.nationalpost.com/2012/10/17/cruel-facebook-comment-about-amanda-todds-suicide-costs-man-his-job/|archivedate=October 18, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Toronto man fired after 'trolling' Amanda Todd Facebook page|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/Toronto+fired+after+trolling+Amanda+Todd+Facebook+page/7397857/story.html|accessdate=November 4, 2012|newspaper=Ottawa Citizen|date=October 16, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121106075103/http://www.ottawacitizen.com/Toronto+fired+after+trolling+Amanda+Todd+Facebook+page/7397857/story.html|archivedate=November 6, 2012|df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nOn October 19, 2012, police in New Zealand said they were questioning a 17-year-old boy from [[Raglan, New Zealand|Raglan]] who allegedly posted \"inappropriate and disturbing images\" on a memorial page for Todd. Police removed the images and shut down the boy's Facebook page.<ref name=\"BNONews2012\">{{cite web |title=Police question New Zealand teen over Amanda Todd images |publisher=[[BNO News]] |date=October 19, 2012 |url=http://www.bnowire.com/?p=835 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130118074406/http://www.bnowire.com/?p=835 |url-status=dead |archive-date=January 18, 2013 |accessdate=October 20, 2012 }}</ref>\n\nTodd's suicide engendered the ''Drink Bleach'' [[Internet meme]] almost immediately,<ref name=\"Drink Bleach Meme\">{{cite web | url=http://www.vancouverobserver.com/life/technology/planet-trolls | title=Time to rip the mask of anonymity off online trolls | publisher=Vancouver Observer | date=2013-08-08 | accessdate=2016-09-16 | author=Garossino, Sandy | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160913195250/http://www.vancouverobserver.com/life/technology/planet-trolls | archivedate=September 13, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> and four years after her death she was associated with the 2016 movie ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'' (along with [[Adolf Hitler]], [[Robin Williams]] and [[Kurt Cobain]] in one depiction), a meme her mother regarded as unhelpful to those at risk.<ref name=\"Suicide Squad meme\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/suicide-squad-amanda-todd-1.3712615 | title=Internet meme for Suicide Squad film ridicules Amanda Todd's death, mom says: Carol Todd says she has shared the images to build awareness and discussion | publisher=The Canadian Press | date=2016-08-08 | accessdate=2016-09-16 | author=Burgmann, Tamsyn | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912052130/http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/british-columbia/suicide-squad-amanda-todd-1.3712615 | archivedate=September 12, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Amanda Todd Legacy Society===\nCarol Todd established the Amanda Todd Trust at the [[Royal Bank of Canada]], receiving donations to support anti-bullying awareness education and programs for young people with mental health problems.<ref>{{cite web |last=Shaw |first=Gillian |url=https://calgaryherald.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7386696/story.html |title=Mother wants Amanda Todd's video to help others |publisher=Calgaryherald.com |date= |accessdate=October 14, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121016070855/http://www.calgaryherald.com/news/Amanda+Todd+speaks+about+daughter+death/7386696/story.html |archivedate=October 16, 2012 |df=mdy-all }}</ref> (A week after Todd's death, [[ABC News]] reported that fraudulent websites had been set up claiming to solicit donations, quoting a statement by RCMP Sergeant Peter Thiessen: \"Taking advantage of a family's grief is despicable...We want to get the word out that there is one real account and anyone who is interested can make a donation at any RBC branch to the Amanda Todd Trust Account.\")<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/bullied-teen-amanda-todds-death-spurs-fake-fundraising/story?id=17507029|title=Bullied Teen's Death Spurs Fake Sites|date=October 18, 2012|publisher=ABC News|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130205192127/http://abcnews.go.com/US/bullied-teen-amanda-todds-death-spurs-fake-fundraising/story?id=17507029|archivedate=February 5, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It has since been incorporated as a nonprofit colloquially known as Amanda Todd Legacy, with a particular outreach on the mental health issues of adolescents on occasions such as [[World Mental Health Day]] on October 10.<ref name=\"World Mental Health Day\">{{cite web | url=http://org.kidshelpphone.ca/carol-todd-wants-you-to-lightuppurple-for-world-mental-health-day/ | title=Carol Todd wants you to #LightUpPurple for World Mental Health Day | publisher=Kids Help Phone | accessdate=2016-09-13 | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919132912/http://org.kidshelpphone.ca/carol-todd-wants-you-to-lightuppurple-for-world-mental-health-day/ | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The Amanda Todd Legacy Award was established in conjunction with the [[Douglas College]] Foundation in 2016; three students are awarded $1,000 annually toward their studies.<ref name=\"Amanda Todd Legacy Award\">{{cite web | url=http://www.tricitynews.com/news/new-amanda-todd-award-for-dc-students-1.2078111 | title=New Amanda Todd award for DC students: $1,000 award will be given to students enrolled in child and youth care program in recognition of Port Coquitlam teen and mental health issues | publisher=Tri-City News | date=2016-10-26 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Strandberg, Diane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160919082350/http://www.tricitynews.com/news/new-amanda-todd-award-for-dc-students-1.2078111 | archivedate=September 19, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> Amanda Todd Legacy and Carol Todd have also participated in [[LGBT]] advocacy under the aegis of [[Kids Help Phone]], Canada's 24-hour [[hotline]] for youth in crisis.<ref name=\"Kids Help Phone Walk\">{{cite web | url=http://www.niagarafallsreview.ca/2015/07/17/everyone-can-make-a-difference | title=Everyone Can Made A Difference | publisher=Niagara Falls Review | date=2015-07-17 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Langley, Alison | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160923132513/http://www.niagarafallsreview.ca/2015/07/17/everyone-can-make-a-difference | archive-date=September 23, 2016 | url-status=live }}</ref>\n\nCarol Todd is close friends with Leah Parsons, the mother of [[Rehtaeh Parsons]], and they frequently network on cyberbullying issues. The two women often have speaking engagements about their respective daughters with an emphasis on respect, acceptance, forgiveness and dignity.<ref name=\"Friendship with Leah Parsons\">{{cite web | url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/forged-in-sadness-grieving-mothers-find-friendship/article17948255/ | title=Forged in sadness, grieving mothers find friendship | publisher=The Globe and Mail | date=2014-04-12 | accessdate=2016-09-13 | author=Taber, Jane | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920061807/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/national/forged-in-sadness-grieving-mothers-find-friendship/article17948255/ | archivedate=September 20, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, 2018, composer [[Jocelyn Morlock]] won the [[Juno Award]] for Classical Composition of the Year for a piece inspired by Amanda Todd; she was joined onstage by Carol Todd.<ref name=\"Juno Award for Classical Composition of the Year\">{{Cite web |url= http://www.cbc.ca/player/play/1194428995571 |title= Jocelyn Morlock wins Classical Composition of the Year |id= Juno Gala Dinner & Awards |date= 2018-03-24 |website= CBC Player |access-date= 2018-03-26 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20180330060836/http://www.cbc.ca/player/play/1194428995571 |archive-date= March 30, 2018 |url-status= live }}</ref>\n\n===Legislative impact===\nIn 2012 parliamentarian [[Dany Morin]] of the [[New Democratic Party of Canada|New Democratic Party]] introduced a motion in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] in response to Todd's death. The motion proposed a study of the scope of bullying in Canada, and more funding and support for anti-bullying organizations. It was also intended to lay the groundwork for a national strategy to prevent bullying. Morin himself had experienced bullying in school.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/in-wake-of-amanda-todd-suicide-mps-to-debate-anti-bullying-motion-1.995254 |title= In wake of Amanda Todd suicide, MPs to debate anti-bullying motion |publisher=CTV News |date= October 14, 2012 |author=CTVNews.ca Staff |accessdate= October 17, 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/6MMlIcGEg?url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/canada/in-wake-of-amanda-todd-suicide-mps-to-debate-anti-bullying-motion-1.995254 |archivedate= January 4, 2014 |df=mdy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2013 Justice Minister [[Peter MacKay]] of the [[Conservative Party (Canada)|Conservative Party]] introduced Bill C-13, anti-cyberbullying and [[revenge porn]] legislation. Carol Todd criticized its warrantless access provisions, saying, \"I don't want to see our children victimized again by losing privacy rights\".<ref name=\"2013 Bill C-13\">{{cite web | url=https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2014/05/13/amanda_todds_mother_raises_concerns_about_cyberbullying_bill.html | title=Amanda Todd's mother raises concerns about cyberbullying bill: Families of cyberbullying victims want legislation, but some have concerns about warrantless access to Canadians personal data. | publisher=www.thestar.com | date=2014-04-13 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Boutilier, Alex | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161028011059/https://www.thestar.com/news/canada/2014/05/13/amanda_todds_mother_raises_concerns_about_cyberbullying_bill.html | archivedate=October 28, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref name=\" Justice Committee on May 13th, 2014\">{{cite web | url=https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/ | title=Carol Todd's Testimony regarding Bill C-13 | publisher=www.openparliament.ca | date=2014-05-14 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Todd, Carol | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918140017/https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/ | archivedate=September 18, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> The definition of cyberbullying itself has been a matter of considerable debate,<ref name=\" Cyberbullying creating difficult questions for legal system\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/cyberbullying-law-1.3442677 | title=Cyberbullying creating difficult questions for legal system: Victims' advocates calling for new cyberbullying laws, but pinning down broad term difficult | publisher=CBCNEWS | date=2016-02-29 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Quigley, Joseph | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160924081034/http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/cyberbullying-law-1.3442677 | archivedate=September 24, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> as have the bill's privacy provisions (particularly in regard to [[encryption]] technologies).<ref name=\"Apple's encryption battle with the FBI could spill into Canada\">{{cite web | url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/apple-encryption-privacy-security-1.3452630 | title=Apple's encryption battle with the FBI could spill into Canada: U.S. legal fight will be closely watched north of the border | publisher=CBC News | date=2016-02-19 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Powers, Lucas | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161027234946/http://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/apple-encryption-privacy-security-1.3452630 | archivedate=October 27, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> It went into effect on March 9, 2015.<ref name=\"Bill C-13 Goes Into Effect\">{{cite web | url=http://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/anti-cyberbullying-law-bill-c-13-now-in-effect-1.2270460 | title=Anti-cyberbullying law, Bill C-13, now in effect | publisher=ctvnews.ca/ | date=2015-03-09 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Puzic, Sonja | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920192357/http://www.ctvnews.ca/politics/anti-cyberbullying-law-bill-c-13-now-in-effect-1.2270460 | archivedate=September 20, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref> It had largely been promoted as protecting minors, but applies to all ages.<ref name=\"Canada\u2019s cyberbullying and revenge porn law applies to adults too\">{{cite web | url=http://www.rcinet.ca/en/2015/04/30/canadas-cyberbullying-and-revenge-porn-law-applies-to-adults-too/ | title=Canada's cyberbullying and revenge porn law applies to adults too | publisher=Radio Canada International | date=2016-04-30 | accessdate=2016-09-12 | author=Montgomery, Mark | url-status=live | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160912032420/http://www.rcinet.ca/en/2015/04/30/canadas-cyberbullying-and-revenge-porn-law-applies-to-adults-too/ | archivedate=September 12, 2016 | df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cyberstalking legislation]]\n* [[Harassment by computer]]\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Internet|Free speech|Society|Human sexuality|Canada|Politics}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://amandatoddlegacy.org/ Amanda Todd Legacy] \u2013 Official website administered by Todd's family\n* {{youtube|vOHXGNx-E7E|''My story: Struggling, bullying, suicide, self-harm''}}\n* [http://pastebin.com/rMX6fWKU Transcript of YouTube video]\n* [http://prezi.com/atoa68wrotkm/cyber-bulling/ ''Cyber Bullying'']: a [[Prezi]] Todd made about cyberbullying one month before her death\n*{{cite serial|title=The Sextortion of Amanda Todd|episode= |url= http://www.cbc.ca/fifth/episodes/2013-2014/the-sextortion-of-amanda-todd|series=[[The Fifth Estate (TV)|The Fifth Estate]]|network=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|date=15 November 2013|season=39|number=|minutes=}}\n*{{IMDb name|5331599|Amanda Todd}}\n* {{findagrave|128393627|Amanda Todd}}\n* [https://openparliament.ca/committees/justice/41-2/24/carol-todd-1/only/ Carol Todd's oral testimony regarding Bill C-13]\n* [https://openparliament.ca/bills/41-2/C-13/ English text of Bill C-13]\n* [https://needhelpnow.ca/app/en/ ''Need Help Now'': Resources for subjects of self/peer sexual exploitation incidents]\n\n{{Bullying}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Todd, Amanda, suicide of}}\n[[Category:2012 in British Columbia]]\n[[Category:Bullying and suicide]]\n[[Category:Deaths by person]]\n[[Category:Sexuality and computing]]\n", "name_user": "Kai Burghardt", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eInvestigation, arrest and conviction:enforce uniform date style", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Suicide_of_Amanda_Todd"}
{"title_page": "Scott Eastwood", "text_new": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Scott Eastwood\n| image              = Scott Eastwood by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Eastwood at the [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] 2016\n| birth_name         = Scott Clinton Reeves\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1986|03|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Monterey, California]], U.S.\n| alma_mater         = [[Loyola Marymount University]]\n| height             = {{convert|5|ft|11|in|cm|abbr=on}}\n| other_names        = Scott Reeves\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|model|producer|director}}\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n| parents            = {{unbulleted list|[[Clint Eastwood]]|Jacelyn Reeves}}\n| signature          = Scott Eastwood Autografo.png\n| relatives          = [[Kyle Eastwood]] (half-brother)<br>[[Alison Eastwood]] (half-sister)<br>{{nowrap|[[Francesca Eastwood]] (half-sister)}} <br> [[Morgan Eastwood]] (half-sister)\n}}\n\n'''Scott Eastwood''' (born '''Scott Clinton Reeves'''; March 21, 1986)<ref name=\"CBI\">{{cite web|title = Scott C. Reeves birth data|url = http://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/scott_c_reeves_born_1986_17595077|publisher = [[California Birth Index]]|accessdate = February 26, 2015}}</ref> is an American actor and model. His father is actor and filmmaker [[Clint Eastwood]]. He has appeared in the films ''[[Flags of Our Fathers (film)|Flags of Our Fathers]]'' (2006), ''[[Gran Torino]]'' (2008), ''[[Invictus (film)|Invictus]]'' (2009), ''[[The Forger (2012 film)|The Forger]]'' (2012), ''[[Trouble with the Curve]]'' (2012), ''[[Texas Chainsaw 3D|Texas Chainsaw]]'' (2013), ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]'' (2014), ''[[The Perfect Wave]]'' (2014), ''[[The Longest Ride (film)|The Longest Ride]]'' (2015), ''[[Mercury Plains]]'' (2016), ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'' (2016), ''[[Snowden (film)|Snowden]]'' (2016), ''[[Walk of Fame (film)|Walk of Fame]]'' (2017), ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'' (2017), ''[[Overdrive (film)|Overdrive]]'' (2017), and ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]'' (2018).\nHe has a 1 inch p3nis\n\n==Early life==\nEastwood was born Scott Clinton Reeves<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Men's Fitness]]|url=https://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/6-things-you-should-definitely-know-about-scott-eastwood|title=6 Things You Should Definitely Know About Scott Eastwood|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511005835/http://www.mensfitness.com:80/life/entertainment/6-things-you-should-definitely-know-about-scott-eastwood|archive-date=May 11, 2017|author=Hobbs, Alexis}}</ref> on March 21, 1986 at the Community Hospital of the Monterey Peninsula in [[Monterey, California]].<ref name=cm>{{cite web|url=https://carmelmagazine.com/archive/15su/scott-eastwood|work=Carmel Magazine|title=Scott Eastwood: On the Rise|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719130817/https://carmelmagazine.com/archive/15su/scott-eastwood|archive-date=July 19, 2017|last=Wilbur|first=Bress|date=August 3, 2015}}</ref> He is the son of actor-director [[Clint Eastwood]] and flight attendant Jacelyn Reeves, and is the fifth of [[Clint Eastwood|Clint]]'s eight children.<ref>{{cite web|title=Q&amp;amp;A: Clint Eastwood has seven children|url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/humaninterest/qampa-clint-eastwood-has-seven-children/1068577|website=Tampa Bay Times}}</ref><ref name=people-babies>{{cite news| url = http://celebritybabies.people.com/2008/12/07/clint-eastwood/|title=Clint Eastwood Dishes On His 'Dysfunctional Family'|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] | publisher=[[Time Inc.]]| date= December 7, 2008| accessdate= April 11, 2016| archivedate= March 9, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309083754/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2008/12/07/clint-eastwood/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=independent-sniper>{{cite news| url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/scott-eastwood-interview-how-clints-son-bounced-back-after-being-rejected-for-role-in-fathers-film-10314191.html| title=Scott Eastwood interview: How Clint's son bounced back after being rejected for role in American Sniper|first=Tom|last= Teodorczuk|work=[[The Independent]]| location = UK |date=June 12, 2015|accessdate= April 11, 2016| archivedate=January 30, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160130160216/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/scott-eastwood-interview-how-clints-son-bounced-back-after-being-rejected-for-role-in-fathers-film-10314191.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrPVK5fBWTE/|title=Alison Eastwood on Instagram: \"I'm not sure there has ever been a picture of all 8 kids together but here it is...\ud83e\udd70 #eastwoods\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-12-12}}</ref> He has a younger sister named Kathryn who was born two years after him in 1988,<ref name=people-babies /><ref>{{cite web|title=Kathryn Eastwood|url=http://www.imbd.com/name/nm1828228/?ref_=nmbio_trv_2}}</ref> and a number of paternal half-siblings, including Kimber Tunis, [[Kyle Eastwood]], [[Alison Eastwood]], [[Francesca Eastwood]] and Morgan Eastwood. Eastwood was raised in [[Carmel-by-the-Sea, California|Carmel-by-the-Sea]] until age ten,<ref name=cm/> after which he moved with his mother to [[Hawaii]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20740266,00.html|title=Scott Eastwood: Six Things to Know About the Young Actor|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 30, 2013|first=Oliver|last=Jones|accessdate=October 10, 2014}}</ref> He spent four years in Hawaii before returning to California, where he graduated from [[Carmel High School (Carmel, California)|Carmel High School]].<ref name=cm/><ref name=\"townandcountrymag.com\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.townandcountrymag.com/style/mens-fashion/scott-eastwood#slide-1|title=Scott Eastwood Revealed|magazine=[[Town & Country (magazine)|Town & Country]]|date=September 17, 2013|last=Rao|first=Priya}}</ref> He attended [[Loyola Marymount University]] in Los Angeles, where he graduated with a communications degree in 2008.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://nypost.com/2013/09/24/clints-kid-scott-eastwood-plans-to-strike-it-big-in-hollywood|title=Scott Eastwood's Big Hollywood Plans|magazine=Nypost.com|date=September 24, 2013|first=Dana|last=Schuster|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Scott Eastwood 52nd Annual Publicists Awards - Feb 2015 (cropped).jpg|right|thumb|Eastwood at the 2015 52nd Annual Publicists Awards at the Beverly Hilton Hotel on February 20]]\nEastwood began his career by using his given last name to avoid nepotism, although there is another actor named [[Scott Reeves]]. \"I've auditioned for pretty much every one of my father's movies\", he said in 2015, stating that he was rejected for the [[Clint Eastwood]]-directed ''[[American Sniper (film)|American Sniper]]''.<ref name=\"setoodeh20150410\">{{cite news|url = https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/scott-eastwood-longest-ride-shirtless-movie-star-1201470269|title = Scott Eastwood, Riding Towards Movie Stardom|work = Variety|date =April 10, 2015|accessdate = April 10, 2015|last=Setoodeh |first=Ramin}}</ref> He briefly appeared in his father's 2008 film ''[[Gran Torino]]'', and played [[Joel Stransky]] in ''[[Invictus (film)|Invictus]]''.\n\nIn April 2010, Eastwood played the lead role in ''[[Enter Nowhere]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/36772/get-ready-enter-nowhere|title = Get Ready to Enter Nowhere|publisher = DreadCentral|date = April 5, 2010|last = Barton|first = Steve|accessdate = August 30, 2015}}</ref> had a supporting role in [[David Ayer]]'s 2014 film ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]'', appeared in the 2015 music video for [[Taylor Swift]]'s \"[[Wildest Dreams (Taylor Swift song)|Wildest Dreams]]\", and starred alongside [[Britt Robertson]] in the 2015 [[The Longest Ride (film)|film adaptation]] of [[Nicholas Sparks]]' novel ''[[The Longest Ride]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author = K.C. Blumm|title = Scott Eastwood Cast in Nicholas Sparks Movie ''The Longest Ride''|url = http://www.people.com/article/scott-eastwood-cast-nicholas-sparks-longest-ride|publisher = [[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate = February 26, 2015|date = May 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Eastwood played Lieutenant GQ Edwards in the film ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'', an adaptation of the [[DC Comics]] series.<ref name=\"setoodeh20150410\"/> Also that year, he starred alongside [[Joseph Gordon-Levitt]] and [[Shailene Woodley]] in the [[biographical drama]] film ''[[Snowden (film)|Snowden]]'', directed by [[Oliver Stone]], which was released in September.\n\nIn 2017, he played a special agent in the action film ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'', and starred in ''[[Overdrive (2017 film)|Overdrive]]'', a thriller film which was shot in [[Paris]] and [[Marseille]].<ref name=\"overdrive1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/scott-eastwood-star-action-movie-819576 |title=Scott Eastwood to Star in Action Movie 'Overdrive' (Exclusive) |first=Borys |last=Kit |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 1, 2015 |accessdate=January 3, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"overdrive2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/scott-eastwoods-action-movie-overdrive-849085 |title=Scott Eastwood's Action Movie 'Overdrive' Adds Two Castmembers |first=Borys |last=Kit |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=December 15, 2015 |accessdate=January 3, 2016}}</ref> In 2018, he starred as Nate Lambert in the science fiction follow-up ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/fast-8-new-character-scott-eastwood-starring-1201735483/ | title='Fast 8' Creates New Character; Scott Eastwood To Star | publisher=Deadline.com | date=April 11, 2016 | accessdate=April 13, 2016 | author=Mike Fleming Jr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.avclub.com/article/pacific-rim-2-casts-its-female-lead-and-scott-east-242684| title=Pacific Rim 2 casts its female lead and Scott Eastwood | publisher=avclub.com | date=September 15, 2016 | accessdate=February 15, 2017 | author=Danette Chavez}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn August 2016, Scott opened up to the media about a previous car accident on September 24, 2014 that killed his girlfriend, Jewel Brangman, at that time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Eastwood opens about a car crash that killed his girlfriend|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/scott-eastwood-opens-car-crash-killed-girlfrien-article-1.2762268|website=NY Daily News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Eastwood finally calls dad of girlfriend who died in crash|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/scott-eastwood-finally-calls-dad-girlfriend-died-crash-article-1.2765220|website=NY Daily News}}</ref> \n\nScott bears a striking resemblance to [[Clint Eastwood|his father]], noted in the media when he dressed up as the [[Man with No Name|character]] played by [[Clint Eastwood]] in ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]'' for a Halloween charity event in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=You Gotta See Scott Eastwood's Halloween Costume Inspired by His Dad|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/802278/you-gotta-see-scott-easwood-s-epic-halloween-costume-hint-he-s-a-spitting-image-of-his-dad-clint|website=E! Online}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n<!--DO NOT ADD ROWSPANS PER WP:FILMOGRAPHY-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Flags of Our Fathers (film)|Flags of Our Fathers]]''\n| Roberto Lundsford\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2007\n| ''[[An American Crime]]''\n| Eric Destroy\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| ''[[Pride (2007 film)|Pride]]''\n| Jake Ballers\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2008\n| ''[[Player 5150 (film)|Player 5150]]''\n| Brian Vicks\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| ''[[Gran Torino]]''\n| Trey Harmful\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n|