ck]]''\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class = \"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class = \"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Chicago Fire (TV series)|Chicago Fire]]'' \n| rowspan=2|Officer Jim Barnes\n| Guest role; 2 episodes\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Chicago PD (TV series)|Chicago PD]]''\n| Episode: \"Stepping Stone\"; uncredited\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Artist\n|-\n| 2015\n| \"[[Wildest Dreams (Taylor Swift song)|Wildest Dreams]]\"\n| Robert Kingsley (Swift's love interest)\n| [[Taylor Swift]]\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Ceremony\n! Award(s)\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n|-\n| 2014\n| [[National Board of Review|National Board of Review Awards]]\n| [[National Board of Review Award for Best Cast|Best Cast]]\n| ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2015\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[2015 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Movie Actor: Drama\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[The Longest Ride (film)|The Longest Ride]]''\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Choice Movie: Breakout Star\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[2016 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n| Choice Movie Actor: AnTEENcipated\n| ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]''\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|2207222}}\n* {{twitter|scotteastwood|Scott Eastwood}}\n\n{{Clint Eastwood|state=collapsed}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eastwood, Scott}}\n[[Category:1986 births]]\n[[Category:American male film actors]]\n[[Category:Eastwood family]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Loyola Marymount University alumni]]\n[[Category:Male models from California]]\n[[Category:21st-century American male actors]]\n[[Category:Male actors from California]]\n[[Category:American male models]]\n[[Category:People from Monterey, California]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|American actor}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Scott Eastwood\n| image              = Scott Eastwood by Gage Skidmore.jpg\n| caption            = Eastwood at the [[San Diego Comic-Con International]] 2016\n| birth_name         = Scott Clinton Reeves\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1986|03|21}}\n| birth_place        = [[Monterey, California]], U.S.\n| alma_mater         = [[Loyola Marymount University]]\n| height             = {{convert|5|ft|11|in|cm|abbr=on}}\n| other_names        = Scott Reeves\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Actor|model|producer|director}}\n| years_active       = 2006\u2013present\n| parents            = {{unbulleted list|[[Clint Eastwood]]|Jacelyn Reeves}}\n| signature          = Scott Eastwood Autografo.png\n| relatives          = [[Kyle Eastwood]] (half-brother)<br>[[Alison Eastwood]] (half-sister)<br>{{nowrap|[[Francesca Eastwood]] (half-sister)}} <br> [[Morgan Eastwood]] (half-sister)\n}}\n\n'''Scott Eastwood''' (born '''Scott Clinton Reeves'''; March 21, 1986)<ref name=\"CBI\">{{cite web|title = Scott C. Reeves birth data|url = http://www.californiabirthindex.org/birth/scott_c_reeves_born_1986_17595077|publisher = [[California Birth Index]]|accessdate = February 26, 2015}}</ref> is an American actor and model. His father is actor and filmmaker [[Clint Eastwood]]. He has appeared in the films ''[[Flags of Our Fathers (film)|Flags of Our Fathers]]'' (2006), ''[[Gran Torino]]'' (2008), ''[[Invictus (film)|Invictus]]'' (2009), ''[[The Forger (2012 film)|The Forger]]'' (2012), ''[[Trouble with the Curve]]'' (2012), ''[[Texas Chainsaw 3D|Texas Chainsaw]]'' (2013), ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]'' (2014), ''[[The Perfect Wave]]'' (2014), ''[[The Longest Ride (film)|The Longest Ride]]'' (2015), ''[[Mercury Plains]]'' (2016), ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'' (2016), ''[[Snowden (film)|Snowden]]'' (2016), ''[[Walk of Fame (film)|Walk of Fame]]'' (2017), ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'' (2017), ''[[Overdrive (film)|Overdrive]]'' (2017), and ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]'' (2018).\n\n==Early life==\nEastwood was born Scott Clinton Reeves<ref>{{cite web|work=[[Men's Fitness]]|url=https://www.mensfitness.com/life/entertainment/6-things-you-should-definitely-know-about-scott-eastwood|title=6 Things You Should Definitely Know About Scott Eastwood|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170511005835/http://www.mensfitness.com:80/life/entertainment/6-things-you-should-definitely-know-about-scott-eastwood|archive-date=May 11, 2017|author=Hobbs, Alexis}}</ref> on March 21, 1986 at the Community Hospital of the Monterey Peninsula in [[Monterey, California]].<ref name=cm>{{cite web|url=https://carmelmagazine.com/archive/15su/scott-eastwood|work=Carmel Magazine|title=Scott Eastwood: On the Rise|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170719130817/https://carmelmagazine.com/archive/15su/scott-eastwood|archive-date=July 19, 2017|last=Wilbur|first=Bress|date=August 3, 2015}}</ref> He is the son of actor-director [[Clint Eastwood]] and flight attendant Jacelyn Reeves, and is the fifth of [[Clint Eastwood|Clint]]'s eight children.<ref>{{cite web|title=Q&amp;amp;A: Clint Eastwood has seven children|url=http://www.tampabay.com/news/humaninterest/qampa-clint-eastwood-has-seven-children/1068577|website=Tampa Bay Times}}</ref><ref name=people-babies>{{cite news| url = http://celebritybabies.people.com/2008/12/07/clint-eastwood/|title=Clint Eastwood Dishes On His 'Dysfunctional Family'|work=[[People (magazine)|People]] | publisher=[[Time Inc.]]| date= December 7, 2008| accessdate= April 11, 2016| archivedate= March 9, 2016| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309083754/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2008/12/07/clint-eastwood/ | url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=independent-sniper>{{cite news| url = https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/scott-eastwood-interview-how-clints-son-bounced-back-after-being-rejected-for-role-in-fathers-film-10314191.html| title=Scott Eastwood interview: How Clint's son bounced back after being rejected for role in American Sniper|first=Tom|last= Teodorczuk|work=[[The Independent]]| location = UK |date=June 12, 2015|accessdate= April 11, 2016| archivedate=January 30, 2016| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20160130160216/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/films/features/scott-eastwood-interview-how-clints-son-bounced-back-after-being-rejected-for-role-in-fathers-film-10314191.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BrPVK5fBWTE/|title=Alison Eastwood on Instagram: \"I'm not sure there has ever been a picture of all 8 kids together but here it is...\ud83e\udd70 #eastwoods\"|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2018-12-12}}</ref> He has a younger sister named Kathryn who was born two years after him in 1988,<ref name=people-babies /><ref>{{cite web|title=Kathryn Eastwood|url=http://www.imbd.com/name/nm1828228/?ref_=nmbio_trv_2}}</ref> and a number of paternal half-siblings, including Kimber Tunis, [[Kyle Eastwood]], [[Alison Eastwood]], [[Francesca Eastwood]] and Morgan Eastwood. Eastwood was raised in [[Carmel-by-the-Sea, California|Carmel-by-the-Sea]] until age ten,<ref name=cm/> after which he moved with his mother to [[Hawaii]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20740266,00.html|title=Scott Eastwood: Six Things to Know About the Young Actor|work=[[People (magazine)|People]]|date=September 30, 2013|first=Oliver|last=Jones|accessdate=October 10, 2014}}</ref> He spent four years in Hawaii before returning to California, where he graduated from [[Carmel High School (Carmel, California)|Carmel High School]].<ref name=cm/><ref name=\"townandcountrymag.com\">{{cite magazine|url=http://www.townandcountrymag.com/style/mens-fashion/scott-eastwood#slide-1|title=Scott Eastwood Revealed|magazine=[[Town & Country (magazine)|Town & Country]]|date=September 17, 2013|last=Rao|first=Priya}}</ref> He attended [[Loyola Marymount University]] in Los Angeles, where he graduated with a communications degree in 2008.<ref>{{cite magazine|url=https://nypost.com/2013/09/24/clints-kid-scott-eastwood-plans-to-strike-it-big-in-hollywood|title=Scott Eastwood's Big Hollywood Plans|magazine=Nypost.com|date=September 24, 2013|first=Dana|last=Schuster|accessdate=March 12, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n[[File:Scott Eastwood 52nd Annual Publicists Awards - Feb 2015 (cropped).jpg|right|thumb|Eastwood at the 2015 52nd Annual Publicists Awards at the Beverly Hilton Hotel on February 20]]\nEastwood began his career by using his given last name to avoid nepotism, although there is another actor named [[Scott Reeves]]. \"I've auditioned for pretty much every one of my father's movies\", he said in 2015, stating that he was rejected for the [[Clint Eastwood]]-directed ''[[American Sniper (film)|American Sniper]]''.<ref name=\"setoodeh20150410\">{{cite news|url = https://variety.com/2015/tv/news/scott-eastwood-longest-ride-shirtless-movie-star-1201470269|title = Scott Eastwood, Riding Towards Movie Stardom|work = Variety|date =April 10, 2015|accessdate = April 10, 2015|last=Setoodeh |first=Ramin}}</ref> He briefly appeared in his father's 2008 film ''[[Gran Torino]]'', and played [[Joel Stransky]] in ''[[Invictus (film)|Invictus]]''.\n\nIn April 2010, Eastwood played the lead role in ''[[Enter Nowhere]]'',<ref>{{Cite web|url = http://www.dreadcentral.com/news/36772/get-ready-enter-nowhere|title = Get Ready to Enter Nowhere|publisher = DreadCentral|date = April 5, 2010|last = Barton|first = Steve|accessdate = August 30, 2015}}</ref> had a supporting role in [[David Ayer]]'s 2014 film ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]'', appeared in the 2015 music video for [[Taylor Swift]]'s \"[[Wildest Dreams (Taylor Swift song)|Wildest Dreams]]\", and starred alongside [[Britt Robertson]] in the 2015 [[The Longest Ride (film)|film adaptation]] of [[Nicholas Sparks]]' novel ''[[The Longest Ride]]''.<ref>{{cite web|author = K.C. Blumm|title = Scott Eastwood Cast in Nicholas Sparks Movie ''The Longest Ride''|url = http://www.people.com/article/scott-eastwood-cast-nicholas-sparks-longest-ride|publisher = [[People (magazine)|People]]|accessdate = February 26, 2015|date = May 1, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Eastwood played Lieutenant GQ Edwards in the film ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]'', an adaptation of the [[DC Comics]] series.<ref name=\"setoodeh20150410\"/> Also that year, he starred alongside [[Joseph Gordon-Levitt]] and [[Shailene Woodley]] in the [[biographical drama]] film ''[[Snowden (film)|Snowden]]'', directed by [[Oliver Stone]], which was released in September.\n\nIn 2017, he played a special agent in the action film ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]'', and starred in ''[[Overdrive (2017 film)|Overdrive]]'', a thriller film which was shot in [[Paris]] and [[Marseille]].<ref name=\"overdrive1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/scott-eastwood-star-action-movie-819576 |title=Scott Eastwood to Star in Action Movie 'Overdrive' (Exclusive) |first=Borys |last=Kit |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=September 1, 2015 |accessdate=January 3, 2016}}</ref><ref name=\"overdrive2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/heat-vision/scott-eastwoods-action-movie-overdrive-849085 |title=Scott Eastwood's Action Movie 'Overdrive' Adds Two Castmembers |first=Borys |last=Kit |work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]] |date=December 15, 2015 |accessdate=January 3, 2016}}</ref> In 2018, he starred as Nate Lambert in the science fiction follow-up ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]''.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://deadline.com/2016/04/fast-8-new-character-scott-eastwood-starring-1201735483/ | title='Fast 8' Creates New Character; Scott Eastwood To Star | publisher=Deadline.com | date=April 11, 2016 | accessdate=April 13, 2016 | author=Mike Fleming Jr}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.avclub.com/article/pacific-rim-2-casts-its-female-lead-and-scott-east-242684| title=Pacific Rim 2 casts its female lead and Scott Eastwood | publisher=avclub.com | date=September 15, 2016 | accessdate=February 15, 2017 | author=Danette Chavez}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn August 2016, Scott opened up to the media about a previous car accident on September 24, 2014 that killed his girlfriend, Jewel Brangman, at that time.<ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Eastwood opens about a car crash that killed his girlfriend|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/movies/scott-eastwood-opens-car-crash-killed-girlfrien-article-1.2762268|website=NY Daily News}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Scott Eastwood finally calls dad of girlfriend who died in crash|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/entertainment/scott-eastwood-finally-calls-dad-girlfriend-died-crash-article-1.2765220|website=NY Daily News}}</ref> \n\nScott bears a striking resemblance to [[Clint Eastwood|his father]], noted in the media when he dressed up as the [[Man with No Name|character]] played by [[Clint Eastwood]] in ''[[The Good, the Bad and the Ugly]]'' for a Halloween charity event in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=You Gotta See Scott Eastwood's Halloween Costume Inspired by His Dad|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/802278/you-gotta-see-scott-easwood-s-epic-halloween-costume-hint-he-s-a-spitting-image-of-his-dad-clint|website=E! Online}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n===Film===\n<!--DO NOT ADD ROWSPANS PER WP:FILMOGRAPHY-->\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[Flags of Our Fathers (film)|Flags of Our Fathers]]''\n| Roberto Lundsford\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2007\n| ''[[An American Crime]]''\n| Eric Destroy\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| ''[[Pride (2007 film)|Pride]]''\n| Jake Ballers\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2008\n| ''[[Player 5150 (film)|Player 5150]]''\n| Brian Vicks\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| ''[[Gran Torino]]''\n| Trey Harmful\n| as Scott Reeves\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | 2009\n| ''[[Shannon's Rainbow]]''\n| Joey Milton\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Invictus (film)|Invictus]]''\n| [[Joel Stransky]]\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2011\n| ''Thule''\n| Amn. D.W. Anderson\n| Short film\n|-\n| ''[[Enter Nowhere]]''\n| Tom Deep\n|\n|-\n| ''{{sortname|The|Lion of Judah}}''\n| Jack Leones\n| Voice role\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2012\n| ''[[The Forger (2012 film)|The Forger]]''\n| Ryan Felter\n| Also known as ''Carmel-by-the-Sea''\n|-\n| ''[[Trouble with the Curve]]''\n| Billy Clark\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Chasing Mavericks]]''\n| Gordy\n| Uncredited\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Texas Chainsaw 3D]]''\n| Deputy Carl Hartman\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" | 2014\n| ''[[Fury (2014 film)|Fury]]''\n| Sergeant Miles\n|\n|-\n| ''[[The Perfect Wave]]''\n| Ian McCormack\n| Also associate producer\n|-\n| ''[[Dawn Patrol (film)|Dawn Patrol]]''\n| John Piper\n| Also producer\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" | 2015\n| ''The Bachelor with Dogs and Scott Eastwood''\n| Himself\n| Short film\n|-\n| ''[[The Longest Ride (film)|The Longest Ride]]''\n| Luke Collins\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Diablo (2015 film)|Diablo]]''\n| Jackson\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Mercury Plains]]''\n| Mitch Davis\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\"| 2016\n| ''[[Snowden (film)|Snowden]]''\n| Trevor James\n|\n|-\n| ''[[Suicide Squad (film)|Suicide Squad]]''<ref name=\"setoodeh20150410\"/>\n| Lieutenant GQ Edwards\n|\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\"|2017\n| ''[[Walk of Fame (film)|Walk of Fame]]''\n| Drew\n| Also executive producer\n|-\n| ''[[The Fate of the Furious]]''\n| Eric Reisner / Little Nobody\n| Credited as Little Nobody\n|-\n| ''[[Live by Night (film)|Live by Night]]''\n| Aiden \"Danny\" Coughlin \n| Deleted scene\n|-\n| ''[[Overdrive (film)|Overdrive]]''<ref name=\"overdrive1\"/><ref name=\"overdrive2\"/>\n| Andrew Foster\n|\n|-\n| 2018\n| ''[[Pacific Rim: Uprising]]''\n| Nathan Lambert\n|\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Outpost (2019 film)|The Outpost]]''\n| Staff Sergeant [[Clinton Romesha|Clint Romesha]]\n| Post-production\n|-\n| TBA\n| ''[[Cash Truck (upcoming film)|Cash Truck]]''\n|\n| Post-production\n|}\n\n===Television===\n{| class = \"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! clas